text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

atenção! #triggerwarning #gatilho #violenciasexualinfantil - compreendemos que não se trata apenas de cordialidade. avisar que certos assunto serão abordados é colocar a saúde do outro no patamar devido, levando em consideração o peso emocional das coisas.
@conteparalguem é um projeto de combate à violência sexual infantil, se este desenho te incomoda, saiba que ele ilustra um relato verdadeiro. sabemos o quão delicado é este assunto e o quanto é difícil trazê-lo à sociedade. mas precisamos falar sobre a violência sexual infantil!
.
.
.
.
.[não sei bem como resumir a minha história com abusos, nem como começar. e acredito que escrevo isso na intenção de me libertar de algo.
bom, eu não lembro bem, mas acho que eu devia ter de sete a dez anos, não recordo a idade de fato, mas eu lembro que morava eu, meu pai, minha mãe, e minhas duas irmãs em uma casinha pequena, era de taipa. o fato é que um vizinho, ele devia ter uns vinte anos na época, entrava lá no quarto, eu dormia na rede, e com a sua mão tocava na minha vagina. não lembro as sensações que eu tinha, nunca contei aos meus pais, tenho vergonha, e jamais penso em contar algum dia. sei que isso aconteceu mais de uma vez, não lembro quantas. cresci com esse sentimento de culpa. acho que me sinto culpada por ter permitido aquilo. outra vez com esse mesmo vizinho, eu lembro que eu estava brincando com outros colegas numa mesa e esse homem estava debaixo dela, e com isso, ele tocou os seus dedos na minha vagina durante a brincadeira, por muitas horas, e desse dia lembro também que eu senti sensações, sinto mais culpa ainda. a minha psicóloga já disse que é natural as crianças sentirem sensações quando são tocadas. lembro que no fim da tarde fui fazer xixi, e mal conseguia, porque tudo ardia. lembro vagamente também de outro acontecido de abuso, dessa vez com outro vizinho, que devia ter a mesma idade que esse, e eu uns treze. na minha casa não tinha tv, então eu e minhas irmãs íamos assistir na casa das pessoas que moravam perto, e uma dessas casas era na casa da mãe desse vizinho...] .

@conteparalguem é um projeto de combate à violência sexual infantil, se este desenho te incomoda, saiba que ele ilustra um relato verdadeiro. sabemos o quão delicado é este assunto e o quanto é difícil trazê-lo à sociedade. mas precisamos falar sobre a violência sexual infantil!
.
.
.
.
.[não sei bem como resumir a minha história com abusos, nem como começar. e acredito que escrevo isso na intenção de me libertar de algo.
bom, eu não lembro bem, mas acho que eu devia ter de sete a dez anos, não recordo a idade de fato, mas eu lembro que morava eu, meu pai, minha mãe, e minhas duas irmãs em uma casinha pequena, era de taipa. o fato é que um vizinho, ele devia ter uns vinte anos na época, entrava lá no quarto, eu dormia na rede, e com a sua mão tocava na minha vagina. não lembro as sensações que eu tinha, nunca contei aos meus pais, tenho vergonha, e jamais penso em contar algum dia. sei que isso aconteceu mais de uma vez, não lembro quantas. cresci com esse sentimento de culpa. acho que me sinto culpada por ter permitido aquilo. outra vez com esse mesmo vizinho, eu lembro que eu estava brincando com outros colegas numa mesa e esse homem estava debaixo dela, e com isso, ele tocou os seus dedos na minha vagina durante a brincadeira, por muitas horas, e desse dia lembro também que eu senti sensações, sinto mais culpa ainda. a minha psicóloga já disse que é natural as crianças sentirem sensações quando são tocadas. lembro que no fim da tarde fui fazer xixi, e mal conseguia, porque tudo ardia. lembro vagamente também de outro acontecido de abuso, dessa vez com outro vizinho, que devia ter a mesma idade que esse, e eu uns treze. na minha casa não tinha tv, então eu e minhas irmãs íamos assistir na casa das pessoas que moravam perto, e uma dessas casas era na casa da mãe desse vizinho...] .
.
.

#blackhistorymonth
#repost from @equalityequation 
#taranaburke's career has been spent uniting us; #metoo allowed 19 million people across 85 countries to declare that we've been affected by sexual violence. @girlsforgenderequity, the non-profit she founded, creates opportunities for young women and girls to live self-determined lives by tackling the many obstacles young women and girls face such as sexism, racial inequality, homophobia, transphobia, and sexual harassment. her most recent work with the #muterkelly movement has allowed the rest of the world to connect to the scores of black women who have, until now, had to stand in silence as the violence, manipulation and abuse they suffered went ignored, and r kelly's wealth built. her involvement in the project has opened us to the prevalence of sexual violence, to its insidiousness, and to our ability to heal each other when we choose to #believewomen. 
for teaching us how to listen and for her work ending the suffering in silence, this #blackhistorymonth we honor @taranajaneen
.

text:
when you were young 🖤

i had some adolescent healing to do this week with this song. when you were young came to me at a very weird time. i was hung up on a guy. i felt betrayed by friends. i wanted to run away and i got my wish but my wish didn’t turn out to be what i expected it to be. in this wish i faced a very ugly incident along with the shadows of racism within this country. the more i heal from what happened to me the more i believe it was meant to be. luckily i have gotten to a place where i can say this. i had to go all out for this song in the honor of every survivor and the oppressed in this country✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿 #brownpride #blacklivesmatter #webelievesurvivors #whyididntreport #lgbtqally #fuckdonaldtrump #metoo

text:
ela sempre prefere estar comigo
.
são muitos abraços e beijos que o cercam. mas ela prefere sempre os meus.
braços se oferecem para terem ela no colo. mas sinto que para ela não há colo no mundo mais macio e acolhedor do que o meu.
ela sorri para muita gente. tem o sorriso doce é fácil. ah, mas o sorriso mais bonito é sempre quando me vê. 
ela gosta de dormir comigo, cantar comigo. estar comigo. 
muita gente não entende e até reprova, mas como poderia ser diferente?
ela sabe, ela sente. quando todos se vão, quando ninguém sabe o que fazer quando ele chora, sou eu que fico. 
quando todos se entregam ao sono profundo, sou eu que sempre estou em estado de alerta para o que ele precisar. e isso ninguém vê. isso ninguém sente. só ela.
essa preferência é nada mais nada menos do que uma forma de gratidão. 
bebês não falam mas são sábios e encontram sempre uma forma de se comunicar. 
e por mais que seja incrível porém exaustivo ser o mundo para ela, eu quero que ela saiba:
filha, entre todos eu prefiro você! .

tweet_full:
ela sempre prefere estar comigo
.
são muitos abraços e beijos que o cercam. mas ela prefere sempre os meus.
braços se oferecem para terem ela no colo. mas sinto que para ela não há colo no mundo mais macio e acolhedor do que o meu.
ela sorri para muita gente. tem o sorriso doce é fácil. ah, mas o sorriso mais bonito é sempre quando me vê. 
ela gosta de dormir comigo, can notar comigo. estar comigo. 
muita gente não entende e até reprova, mas como poderia ser diferente?
ela sabe, ela sente. quando todos se vão, quando ninguém sabe o que fazer quando ele chora, sou eu que fico. 
quando todos se entregam ao sono profundo, sou eu que sempre estou em estado de alerta para o que ele precisar. e isso ninguém vê. isso ninguém sente. só ela.
essa preferência é nada mais nada menos do que uma forma de gratidão. 
bebês não falam mas são sábios e encontram sempre uma forma de se comunicar. 
e por mais que seja incrível porém exaustivo ser o mundo para ela, eu quero que ela saiba:
filha, entre todos eu prefiro você! .

text:
when a manager is exhibiting toxic behavior at work it can feel overwhelming. too often the fear of repercussion keeps workers silent from voicing concerns.

if there isn’t a safe channel for employees to report bad behavior, it is impossible for management to have full visibility into the issues that need to be addressed.

warble wants to change this. we let employees anonymously report bad behavior directly to the offender’s boss at
www.warble.work

once multiple people identify someone as disruptive, the direct manager is notified.

keep everyone accountable to the same standards at work. anonymously report disruptive behavior.

text:
because when a woman is loved correctly and feels safe?  she becomes 10 times the woman she was before. 
the movies and the books don’t teach us to see those that amplify us, they teach us chemistry.  which eventually fades and then what?

all those times you’ve been told you’re too much? 
you’re just being guided to level up 
what if you were more attentive to cues of safety- of the ability to be yourself quirks and all?
what if you were more attentive to how he shows up- is he showing up as a flame out or more?
we would be more.  we would be amplified. and we would fill our own cups easier ❤️💕💚💗

text:
#taranaburke's career has been spent uniting us; #metoo allowed 19 million people across 85 countries to declare that we've been affected by sexual violence. just be, the non-profit she founded, focusing on the health, well-being, and wholeness of young women of color, sought to empower and provide guidance to girls as they begin to define themselves. her most recent work with the #muterkelly movement has allowed the rest of the world to connect to the scores of black women who have, until now, had to stand in silence as the violence, manipulation and abuse they suffered went ignored, and r kelly's wealth built. her involvement in the project has opened us to the prevalence of sexual violence, to its insidiousness, and to our ability to heal each other when we choose to #believewomen. 
for teaching us how to listen and for her work ending the suffering in silence, this #blackhistorymonth we honor @taranajaneen
.

text:
🎉🎉 know your rights is here!! 🎉🎉 (link in profile)
.

a midwife seemed like a good fit for me until she told me i needed to schedule an induction once i went past 41 weeks.  i never got a good reason why.
.
so, at 41 weeks and 6 days pregnant, with the help of my doula, i switched to a different hospital and midwife, who was willing to lay out all my options and support me in my *free* choice about what i wanted to do.  i was really lucky to find a care provider who was willing to take me that late in pregnancy.  i ended up having my baby the very next day with no complications in a respectful environment with no unnecessary medical intervention.
.
but i didn’t really know my rights.  i didn’t really think i *needed* to know my rights--until i got in hot water.
.
everything worked out just fine, but the whole thing left me with a lot of questions about my own rights in that situation. what might have happened if another care provider hadn’t turned up for me?  what rights did i have to stand on, what rights belonged to me, to protect myself and my baby? .
the more i researched and spoke with other people who had given birth, the more surprised i was to realize what strong rights i had had to say no, and how commonly that right is violated in maternity care.
.
that was seven years ago!  today, i'm releasing know your rights: legal and human rights in childbirth for birth professionals & advocates (link in profile)--a product of years working with top lawyers and advocates trying to untangle this dilemma.  it's a must for anyone working in birth.  period.
.

#midwife #nursemidwife #laboranddelivery #birth #pregnancylife

text:
creo que nací siendo feminista, me rebelé ante toda imposición patriarcal y aunque también siga reeducándome por tener conductas machistas, fui una rebelde en toda regla. siempre luchando contra aquello que consideraba injusto, no había quién me frenara. lo pueden corroborar los profesores que lo padecieron. no he cambiado tanto. 
sin quererlo comencé a reeducarme en el feminismo. leyendo libros descubrí que la historia no era como me la habían contado y que faltaban muchos nombres de mujeres importantes que no había estudiado. además, con mi esperanza de querer cambiar el mundo desde niña, encontrar referentes femeninos me parecía todavía mejor.

actualmente el feminismo, la reeducación, el activismo, la sororidad y el debate forman parte de mi vida diaria. sí, el feminismo te cambia la vida, a mejor. aleja a las personas tóxicas que tienen mentes cerradas y te acerca a otras mucho más valientes de todo el mundo que aportan mucho más a la vida. incluso desde la otra punta del planeta.

me sorprendo a mí misma hablando a diario con feministas de cantidad de países y ciudades del mundo. contando nuestras experiencias sin vergüenza, destapando aquello que nos hemos callado años, encontrando apoyo en otras mujeres a las que ni hemos visto la cara. de verdad, la sororidad es maravillosa y las mujeres que me he encontrado en mi camino feminista todavía más. 
por favor, dejen llevar nuestros valores más allá. permitan que el feminismo cambie el mundo porque la igualdad nos beneficia a todos. se lo aseguro. .
.
.
.
el 8 de marzo no te quedes en casa. no seas inmóvil ante un movimiento mundial que está revolucionando la sociedad actual. si necesitas información, pídela. si quieres compañía, tienes nuestros brazos abiertos. 
el feminismo necesita a todas las mujeres unidas y a los hombres apoyando nuestra lucha. esto es solo el comienzo de todo lo que vamos a lograr. porque el patriarcado no se va a caer, lo vamos a tirar.

text:
att använda sin frustration i olika sammanhang för att förändra. att så frön hos omgivningen. 
för min del är det frustrerande att kvinnor fortfarande är det andra könet. att kvinnor fortfarande tjänar betydligt sämre, att kvinnor i sverige ligger så mycket efter -jobbar gratis 54min per dag i jämförelse med män! att kvinnor fortfarande är dubbelarbetande (drar största lasset hemma med barn, relation etc.) att kvinnor utsätts för sexuella övergrepp, avpersonifieras, tillintetgörs, objektifieras, förminskas.........
att en kvinna som blir drogad och våldtagen inte får sitt fall prövat på riktigt trots bevis. att hon sedan ställs inför rätta för att ha droger i kroppen och ifrågasätts av socialen, försäkringskassan mfl. att ständigt som kvinna behöva vara på sin vakt! att vårt rättssamhälle bygger på män och inte är rättssäkert för kvinnor. att våldtäktsfall ständigt läggs ner och att straffen för våldäkt och barn och kvinnomisshandel är gör låga... jag kan fortsätta i oändligheten. 
jag lyfter dessa frågor mycket på min arbetsplats för att väcka tankarna hos de kollegor som har privilegiet att aldrig behöva reflektera över detta för egen del. (jag har till 80% manliga kollegor)ser faktiskt att jag har startat något! jag har nu sått så många frön och vattnat dessa under en god tid att de börjar växa! 
på lunchen idag reflekterades det mkt bland de fem män jag lunchade med om hur vårt patriarkala samhälle påverkat dem i sina relationer och vem som gör vad...
insikt är ett första steg mot förändring! hur våra barns pappor är och beter sig smittar till våra barn och kan jag påverkar i det ”lilla” kan även du! 
hur gör ni för att förändra något ni är arga och frustrerade över?

text: i never expected to look naked in this picture as i just pulled down my straps on my costume but amazing how posing can cover certain areas 🤷🏼‍♀️ honestly don’t know what i’m talking about 😆 anyway, this photo is dedicated to all those people out their that find it difficult to embrace their own bodies. i honestly feel for you especially as someone who had experiences of self body hating for years. i wish i could give everyone the magic fairy dust that helped change my life but this is something you have to do for yourself. it may seem extremely difficult right now but remember that your body is your body and not anyone else’s. if you’re off on holiday and worrying about wearing a bikini on the beach, i hear you. i always planned my day by the pool. i had to sunbathe far away from everyone all the way close to the bushes 😆i made sure there were 2 towels to wrap around me especially for toilet breaks. it was the most planned out event on my calendar. holidays should be easy and they certainly should be relaxed. if it’s any consolation remember this....most people will not bat an eyelid at you and if they do, they’ll be more bothered about getting a tan and having a great time on their holiday. in the famous words of nike ‘just do it’. don’t worry about others, think about you. #bikinifun #bikinilife👙 #bodyempowerment #thisisme #positivevibes #mindsetquotes #bodypositivemovement #lovetheskinyourein #lifestyle #metoo #beautifulwomen #survivor #scarscanswim @lovetheskin_ur_in @lovetheskinyourein.official @nivea_uk ❤️👌🏼

text:
i'm fine...
_
two words that mask a lot...
_
along with ok...
_
ok... is exactly how i've been lately.
_
how you doing chels?
_
i'm ok...
_
until i broke down yesterday.
_
i had enough.
_
i was fed up being ok...
_
and had to actually say... no i'm not.
_
i cried a lot.. and then guess what? 
_
i really was ok...
_
it's important to allow yourself to check in with what's going on.
_
i'm very good at coping and processing... and have a great awareness about what's going on but what i didn't realise is that for a moment...
_
i forgot to feel.
_
so it was building ... underneath the surface...
_
until it hit me.
_
and guess what, today i woke up... _
stronger, focused and more determined then i have been for awhile.
_
don't forget to feel...
_
you can only move forward when you are whole...
_
the good and the bad.
the love and the hurt.
_
it is all you... and you've got this!
_
(drawing by me, words left by others) ❤️
name: Confidence Coach
tweet_full:
i am fine...
_
two words that mask a lot...
_
along with ok...
_
ok... is exactly how i have been lately.
_
how you doing chels?
_
i am ok...
_
until i broke down yesterday.
_
i had enough.
_
i was fed up being ok...
_
and had to actually say... no i am not.
_
i cried a lot.. and then guess what? 
_
i really was ok...
_
it is important to allow yourself to check in with what's going on.
_
i am very good at coping and processing... and have a great awareness about what's going on but what i didn't realise is that for a moment...
_
i forgot to feel.
_
so it was building ... underneath the surface...
_
until it hit me.
_
and guess what, today i woke up... _
stronger, focused and more determined then i have been for awhile.
_
do not forget to feel...
_
you can only move forward when you are whole...
_
the good and the bad.
the love and the hurt.
_
it is all you... and you have got this!
_
(drawing by me, words left by others) ❤️

text_retweet:
reposted from @_weareher -  a survivor reached out to me the other day and asked if i had forgiven my abuser. i took a second to think and told her that i hadn’t. my answer brought some relief to her. she told me that she didn’t think she’d ever be able to forgive her abuser and heard that forgiveness brings peace. more power to anyone who has been able to forgive, it’s not easy and i respect you immensely for being able to do this.

but i’m not forgiving my abuser. he’s taken so much from me: my physical health, my mental health, relationships with others, so much money, and even more time. and to hurt me is one thing, but i know other women who have come forward about the same man. he doesn’t deserve my forgiveness.

and i’m okay with that. i’ve been able to heal despite the fact that i haven’t forgiven him. my life feels complete now and i don’t need the peace that comes with forgiving him in order to move on with my life. we all heal differently and if you feel like you can’t ever forgive the person who hurt you, then don’t. you have that right. 💜💙 #weareher

#heal #empower #restore #survivor #forgiveness #abuser #toxicrelationships #narcissisticabuse #rape #sexualassault #survivorsisters #therapy #healing #healingjourney #movingon #peace #love #abuse #traumasurvivor #metoo #nomore

text:
as long as i could remember i have loved taking picture.  now don’t get me wrong.  i am not a professional and i don’t want to be.  i just like documenting all the things i am doing.  looking back at old photo albums the other day and even some scrapbooks i made in the past was so fun.  every picture tells a story and each story is a memory.  this picture was from our trip to colorado last fall. so beautiful and the memories from that trip are priceless. as a memory care director we use old photos to help trigger a memory, sometimes it works and other times it doesn’t but it was fun to see what they say in regards to the pictures. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
#holisticliving #wellness #wellnessinsideout #agouldstory #fgnaturalwellness #selfcare #metoo #healthyliving #healthyhome #healthyfamilies #memories #thegouldstakecolorado #savememories

text:
ребята, я решила, что пора бы мне как-то оживить профиль в конце-то-концов 😏 и пришла к выводу, что лучшего способа отличиться, нежели как открыть узконаправленную рубрику в своём «недоблоге», не существует. поэтому прошу любить и жаловать мое маленькое (надеюсь, пока что) детище – рубрику #букеровскиечтения 📚 в рамках этой рубрики я (как ни странно) 😅 буду читать авторов, чьи работы были номинированы на букеровскую премию. и первая книга, о которой я бы хотела с вами поговорить, крайне злободневная и откровенно экспериментальная, стала победителем букеровской премии относительно недавно, осенью 2018 года 👏 если вы следите за тем, что происходит в литературном мире, то, должно быть, уже догадались, что речь идёт о «молочнике» анны бёрнс. анна бёрнс – первый лауреат из северной ирландии ☘️ политкорректность или реверанс в сторону феминизма? аль литературное мастерство? за что анна бёрнс получила букера? 🤔 давайте попытаемся разобраться.
⠀
сюжет 🔍 действие романа происходит в неспокойные для северной ирландии 70-е годы, в безымянном городе, в городе, в котором лучше быть незаметным, нежели «интересным». главная героиня романа – восемнадцатилетняя девушка, которая, казалось бы, больше всего на свете жаждет не привлекать к себе внимания, хотя её довольно-таки странная привычка читать романы на ходу говорит об обратном 🤭 и вот представьте, что такая девушка оказывается вовлеченной в странную связь с представителем противоположного пола, с неким «молочником», который вовсе не молочник, а одна из видных фигур военизированной группировки ира 😦 почему связь эта кажется мне странной? да потому что мужчина преследует главную героиню с весьма очевидной целью, но при этом не оставляет девушке ни малейшего повода сообщить о происходящем в полицию. он не то, чтобы девушки пальцем не касается, он даже не смотрит ей в глаза. просто появляется во время её «чтений на ходу», вечерних пробежек или занятий в вечерней школе. при этом «молочник» знает о девушке всё и не стесняется ей об этом говорить – где она живёт, работает, во сколько отправляется на работу, каким автобусом возвращается с работы, знает всё о членах семьи главной героини.
⠀
продолжение в комментариях ⤵️⤵️⤵️

сюжет 🔍 действие романа происходит в неспокойные для северной ирландии 70-е годы, в безымянном городе, в городе, в котором лучше быть незаметным, нежели «интересным». главная героиня романа – восемнадцатилетняя девушка, которая, казалось бы, больше всего на свете жаждет не привлекать к себе внимания, хотя её довольно-таки странная привычка читать романы на ходу говорит об обратном 🤭 и вот представьте, что такая девушка оказывается вовлеченной в странную связь с представителем противоположного пола, с неким «молочником», который вовсе не молочник, а одна из видных фигур военизированной группировки ира 😦 почему связь эта кажется мне странной? да потому что мужчина преследует главную героиню с весьма очевидной целью, но при этом не оставляет девушке ни малейшего повода сообщить о происходящем в полицию. он не то, чтобы девушки пальцем не касается, он даже не смотрит ей в глаза. просто появляется во время её «чтений на ходу», вечерних пробежек или занятий в вечерней школе. при этом «молочник» знает о девушке всё и не стесняется ей об этом говорить – где она живёт, работает, во сколько отправляется на работу, каким автобусом возвращается с работы, знает всё о членах семьи главной героини.
⠀

text:
epistolario.
así se titula el nuevo libro que recoge las cartas inéditas de la gran actriz catalana,  margarita xirgu.

un documento excepcional para conocer la personalidad teatral, política, religiosa, humana y vital de esta gran actriz.

editorial: @renacimientoed 
el libro reproducen todas las cartas escritas por la propia xirgu que hemos podido localizar hasta la fecha y que vienen a iluminar su intimidad más recóndita y su compleja y –naturalmente también– contradictoria personalidad artística y humana. margarita xirgu ha constituido un símbolo en el imaginario colectivo de nuestro exilio republicano de 1939, y ese mito se ha fundamentado tanto en razones escénicas como políticas. en efecto, el nombre de la actriz catalana se ha vinculado con razón al de otro mito antifascista y republicano como es el de federico garcía lorca.
.
.
. .

text:
belen rodriguez, intervistata da la repubblica parla del perchè è partita per l'argentina, proprio ora che sembrava essersi riavvicinata all'ex marito, stefano de martino: "non sono venuta qui per la famiglia. sono in vacanza, avevo bisogno di un po' di tempo per me". e, a domanda diretta su se/come sta procedendo con de martino la showgirl pare non abbia voluto rispondere, anche se il "sono in un momento particolare della mia vita" ha, forse, parlato più di lei. e sarà ancora più eloquente il filmato integrale di belen e stefano, che verrà trasmesso questa sera a # cr4 - la repubblica delle donne condotto da piero chiambretti e alfo signorini. belen ha parlato anche delle continue critiche cui è soggetta: "se sei bella sei anche cretina, non soffri, non provi dispiaceri come le altre donne. ma chi l'ha detto? mi sono stancata di agire con spontaneità e venire travisata". quanto, invece, alle recenti dichiarazioni di rocco papaleo (secondo cui belen durante il festival di sanremo condotto insieme rivolgeva parole solo sul palco): "non è assolutamente vero. chi mi conosce lo sa, io parlo con tutti". un palco, quello dell'ariston, che belen rivedrà a partire da venerdì, essendo nella giuria di sanremo young: "ii festival è il programma a cui sono più affezionata (...), ma non giudicherò, darò la mia opinione ". anche se a livello professionale rimane maria de filippi il suo "mentore": "stare con lei è come fare una seduta di analisi, un'esperienza incredibile senza prezzo". sempre a livello professionale nell'era del #metoo vien da chiedersi e chiederle se sia mai trovata in situazioni di disagio: "mai in situazioni in cui devi scappare.. se un uomo ti apre in accapatoio risolvi non entrando nella stanza " ha risposto la showgirl e conduttrice che sul fututo ha detto "mi piacerebbe avere un altro figlio (dopo santiago che "viene prima di tutto").non voglio che la mia vita sia particolare, voglio che sia normale ".♥️
#belenrodriguez

text:
many of you know that i, besides being an ol’ school music and pop culture nerd, am a(n) adjunct sexuality & gender professor, activist, and dissertating phd candidate.
• • •
aside from that, my longtime friend and colleague dr. jenn pollitt and i just launched our partnership, empathy at work llc (@empathyatworkconsulting). we’ve branded ourselves as a cultural empathy consultancy, providing a range of services from sexual harassment/discrimination and diversity & equity trainings to leadership/management development & coaching, and more.
• • •
our goal? we’re in the business of empowering humans with the skills to better harness their courage in order to grow and nurture their empathetic selves. thus, creating safer spaces for people to connect and collaborate in the workplace and beyond. as we see it, this goes beyond the scope of cultural competence, a level of sociocultural understanding that so many of us in the helping professions (and elsewhere) have been taught is the gold standard for affirming practice.
• • •
we’d love your help in getting the word out about our services and i’d be happy to answer any questions y’all have. also, and this is a big one, we are open and available to traveling for work. have gig, will travel. ☺️ 💕 ✊🏾

text:
international women day 
right now is a great and important time in history to do everything possible to help forge a more gender-balanced world. women have come a long way, yet there's still more to be achieved under the theme: #balanceforbetter is a call-to-action for driving gender balance across the world.

as organisation we believe in championing cause to empower women and girls to overcome every form of limitations and equipped them for leadership and boldness to break barriers in life

our president adigun temitayo mcipsmn, pmp, mba and team present at the annual women event

thanks to lagos state government and ministry of women affairs and poverty allivation in collaboration with saxifrage foundation hosting ngos, cso, private and public organisation including community women leaders to a time out to challenge everyone to fostering initiatives towards empowering women in girls in ngeria under the theme:
fostering harmonize living through reforms and strengthening of social services and substantive equality among women and girls 
the achievement of the ambitious sustainable development goals (sdgs) requires transformative shifts, integrated approaches and new solutions, particularly when it comes to advancing gender equality and the empowerment of all women and girls.

text:
according to the national sexual violence resource center * 1 in 5 women and 1 in 71 men will be raped at some point in their lives.
* in the united stares 1 in 3 women and 1 in 6 men experienced some form of contact sexual violence in their lifetime.
* 51.1% of female victims of rape reported being raped by an intimate partner and 40.8% by an acquaintance.
* 52.4% of male victims report being raped by an acquaintance and 15.1% by a stranger.
* 49.5% of multiracial women and over 45% of american indian/alaska native women were subjected to some form of contact sexual violence in their lifetime.
* 91% of victims of rape and sexual assault are female, and 9% are male * in 8 out of 10 cases of rape, the victim knew the perpetrator.
* 8% of rapes occur while the victim is at work. 
the problem of sexual violence runs rampant, and yet rape is the most under-reported crime; 63% of sexual assaults are not reported to police. of the remaining 37% that are reported less than 10% are instances of false reporting. the facts are clear, and still the culture that would rather victims of sexually based crimes remain silent prevails. 
join rebecca macceile as she throws off the shackles of silence and raises her voice. turquoise boot straps: a survivor’s thoughts provides a glimpse into her journey of self discovery while tackling many controversial topics at the height of the metoo era. #comingsoon #saam #nsvrc #indieauthor #newrelease #pstdsurvivor #metoo available at the #linkinbio april 2019 #newreads #bookstagram

text:
feb 13 my new beginning / new year! 🍀unlucky 13? ☘ nahhhhh 
six years ago i walked into an empty house.  my ex left me for another woman.  this day.... just before valentine's day will forever be like new years eve to me, a reminder not of an ending but a new beginning. 
it reminds me not of how little i was loved but how lucky i have been to have survived both physically in the literal sense and emotionally as well. that man would have killed me or we killed each other.  he used to say "one of these days you're gonna shoot me." he was right.  i was tired of being knocked unconscious or choked out.  i feared one day would be the last day or he would hurt me terribly.  i feared for my life.

i am still working hard to figure it out and still fucking up tremendously... but i am moving forward and the life lessons are worth it.  i am figuring this out little by little.  no more flinching around men.  boundaries strong.  happy, healthy, loved and adored.  my life is blessed. 
#lucky #🍀 #☘ #coachkarma #karmaondeck #abusesirvivor #survivor #metoo #domesticviolence #domestic #live #vegas #boston #chicago #slc #atlanta #nc #philadelphia #massachusetts

text:
orbs, l'autre planète, cette revue "cosmoderne" qui aborde l'humain, la conscience, l'art, la science et la spiritualité.
le prochain numéro sera consacré au feminin.
plus que 7 jours pour pré-commander et/ou faire connaître ce numéro spécial féminin de "orbs, l'autre planète"  qui trace entre autres 20 sujets passionnants, la longue route de la reconnaissance des femmes réalisatrices, des pionnieres comme alice guy-blaché au mouvement @timesupnow, en passant par le weekend des 100 femmes de l'hôtel miramar et le @metoomvmt de @taranajaneen jusqu'à la déferlante 2017 du hashtag #metoo déclenchée par l'actrice @milano_alyssa.

link un bio
https://fr.ulule.com/orbs-feminin/

prenons soin du monde, ensemble, avec amour, celui qui nous relie.

#orbsspécialféminin
#noussommestouselle

ce numéro est crée dans le flux d’une respiration, en se laissant guider à un instant charnière du temps du féminin. dans l’éveil spectaculaire du 21eme siècle sur la question des droits des femmes. où les souffrances de la terre-mère bousculent nos agendas. quand les vieilles mémoires remontent à la surface pour être contemplées et traversées. 
votre soutien contribue à cette mise au monde.

#noussommestouselle
#orbsspécialfémin

text:
💜mi revolución vive en este cuerpo💜
ya no espera
no necesita aprobación ni permiso
sucede porque tiene que suceder en cada vecindario, aldea, ciudad o pueblo en reuniones de tribus, compañeros estudiantes, mujeres en el mercado, en el autobús
puede ser gradual y suave
puede ser espontánea y ruidosa
puede estar ocurriendo ya
se puede encontrar en su armario, sus cajones, sus entrañas, sus piernas, sus células... en la boca desnuda de pezones tensos y senos desbordados 
mi #revolución se está hinchando por la insaciable batería entre mis piernas 
está dispuesta a morir por esto 
está lista para vivir a lo grande
está derrocando el estado de ánimo llamado #patriarcado
no será coreografiada aunque comience con algunos pasos familiares 
no es violenta, pero no se aleja de los peligrosos bordes donde las feroces demostraciones de resistencia caen en algo nuevo
está en este cuerpo 
en estas caderas atrofiadas por la #misoginia 
en esta mandíbula atada por el hambre y la atrocidad
es conexión, no consumo
pasión, sin ganancias
goce, no propiedad 
es de la tierra y vendrá de ella
para ella, por ella 
entiende que cada vez que frackeamos o perforamos o quemamos o violamos las capas de su carácter sagrado,
violamos el alma de nuestro futuro
no se avergüenza de presionar mi cuerpo sobre su piso de barro frente banyans, cypress, pinos, kalyaans, oaks, castaños, secuoyas, sicómoros
viene a inclinarse sin pudor y se levantó cielos parámetro azul, corazón 
explosión púrpura y aqua mar
besa con gusto los pies de las #madres y las enfermeras y los servidores y productos de limpieza y niñeras y #sanadores y todos los que son vida y dar #vida
está en mis rodillas, y de rodillas a cada cosa sagrada
y a aquellos que llevan cargas hechas en el imperio dentro y sobre sus cabezas, espaldas y corazones
exige abandono
aparece
no es ingenua, pero cree en los milagros 
entiende que las divisiones son desviaciones
debo estar quieta y mirarme a los ojos
adelante, 
amor 💜

full video: http://www.vday.org/myrevolutionlivesinthisbody

text:
not everyone deserves the benefit of the doubt. not everyone deserves an opportunity to show they've changed. not everyone deserves a chance. sometimes its best to listen to the horror stories people warn you.

two years ago. i remember two years ago. i had just joined the @sdaffl football league the week prior. i remember i was running the convention center stairs with my football coach & another friend from the football league when i got a text from my then best friend of almost 10yrs. he was super emotional. i headed over after the stairs.

i remember showing up and he was upset punching the walls, angry, screaming, crying over his recent breakup. i started trying to talk him down which had become the norm. after awhile he asked if i wanted a drink. he made me a drink. i remember this straight man trying to make out with me & me pushing him away & saying no over & over again. then i froze. you hear a lot about fight or flight. i froze. 
i remember every second, every moment of my rape, but i remember it as if i wasn't there. i seperated from my body. i remember him saying over and over "you're such a good boy" and "this is a first for me. i've never done this before." i remember showering after in a state of shock not fully realizing what happened. it took me several months to even mention or accept what happened that night. it took a near suicide attempt & being scared to leave my house to accept what happened that night. i remember going to church, showing up to practices, going to the games, going bacl to the gym and hearing people ask what's wrong with you, why are you freaking out, are you ok? two years. two years ago. i remember everything... not everyone deserves the benefit of the doubt.

i'm a better person now. i still freak out sometimes & need my alone time. i still have anxiety. i still have trust issues in relationships. i still have guards up against any intimacy. i'm still not ok, but i'm so much more ok than i've ever been. i know something good will come out of this. so much already has
name: Joalby Phoenix

'i have not done this for material gain.' this is her message to all those who say that women make false accusations for their own benefit.

text:
atenção! #triggerwarning #gatilho #violenciasexualinfantil - compreendemos que não se trata apenas de cordialidade. avisar que certos assunto serão abordados é colocar a saúde do outro no patamar devido, levando em consideração o peso emocional das coisas.
@conteparalguem é um projeto de combate à violência sexual infantil do qual faço parte - desenhando. 
se este desenho te incomoda, saiba que ele ilustra um relato verdadeiro. sabemos o quão delicado é este assunto e o quanto é difícil trazê-lo à sociedade. mas precisamos falar sobre a violência sexual infantil!
.
.
.
.
.[não sei bem como resumir a minha história com abusos, nem como começar. e acredito que escrevo isso na intenção de me libertar de algo.
bom, eu não lembro bem, mas acho que eu devia ter de sete a dez anos, não recordo a idade de fato, mas eu lembro que morava eu, meu pai, minha mãe, e minhas duas irmãs em uma casinha pequena, era de taipa. o fato é que um vizinho, ele devia ter uns vinte anos na época, entrava lá no quarto, eu dormia na rede, e com a sua mão tocava na minha vagina. não lembro as sensações que eu tinha, nunca contei aos meus pais, tenho vergonha, e jamais penso em contar algum dia. sei que isso aconteceu mais de uma vez, não lembro quantas. cresci com esse sentimento de culpa. acho que me sinto culpada por ter permitido aquilo. outra vez com esse mesmo vizinho, eu lembro que eu estava brincando com outros colegas numa mesa e esse homem estava debaixo dela, e com isso, ele tocou os seus dedos na minha vagina durante a brincadeira, por muitas horas, e desse dia lembro também que eu senti sensações, sinto mais culpa ainda. a minha psicóloga já disse que é natural as crianças sentirem sensações quando são tocadas. lembro que no fim da tarde fui fazer xixi, e mal conseguia, porque tudo ardia. lembro vagamente também de outro acontecido de abuso, dessa vez com outro vizinho, que devia ter a mesma idade que esse, e eu uns treze. na minha casa não tinha tv, então eu e minhas irmãs íamos assistir na casa das pessoas que moravam perto, e uma dessas casas era na casa da mãe desse vizinho...] .
.
.
leia na íntegra no facebook da página do conte para alguém. #metoo #rededeapoio

text:
a survivor reached out to me the other day and asked if i had forgiven my abuser. i took a second to think and told her that i hadn’t. my answer brought some relief to her. she told me that she didn’t think she’d ever be able to forgive her abuser and heard that forgiveness brings peace. more power to anyone who has been able to forgive, it’s not easy and i respect you immensely for being able to do this.

but i’m not forgiving my abuser. he’s taken so much from me: my physical health, my mental health, relationships with others, so much money, and even more time. and to hurt me is one thing, but i know other women who have come forward about the same man. he doesn’t deserve my forgiveness.

and i’m okay with that. i’ve been able to heal despite the fact that i haven’t forgiven him. my life feels complete now and i don’t need the peace that comes with forgiving him in order to move on with my life. we all heal differently and if you feel like you can’t ever forgive the person who hurt you, then don’t. you have that right. 💜💙 #weareher

#heal #empower #restore #survivor #forgiveness #abuser #toxicrelationships #narcissisticabuse #rape #sexualassault #survivorsisters #therapy #healing #healingjourney #movingon #peace #love #abuse #traumasurvivor #metoo #nomore

text:
#esquire "журнал esquire в феврале выпустил номер, главной темой которого стала история 17-летнего парня из сша. подросток рассказал, каково это - быть белым гетеросексуальным парнем из среднего класса в эру соцсетей, стрельбы в школах, токсичной маскулинности, движения #metoo и разделённой страны: http://lentach.media/48b4 
в соцсетях и сми журнал раскритиковали (внимание!) за то, что журналисты выбрали в качестве портрета американского подростка именно белого парня, который не представляет ни одно меньшинство." 🤔моё мнение :
я прям респектую журналу. я перенасыщен уже выслушивая мнения и права разных людей в обществе. от толерантности уже раздражает. общество разбито на тысячи осколков. эти попытки перекроить общество сводятся к тому, что во всем виноваты белые мужчины натуралы. (да уродов в этой группе хватает) но среди геев тоже есть откровенные "пидор@сы". и среди феменисток наглухо отбитых немало. и среди всех других меньшинств полно как людей с тяжелыми историями так и конченных, требующих толерантности в каждой дырке.

когда жизнь белого мужчины натурала катиться впизду. все говорят "ну что такого, обычное дело". но если этот мужчина спит с другим мужчиной то "о боги, ублюдошное общество как ты смеешь??? надо помочь ему!!!" я не жалуюсь. люди прикрывающиеся толерантностью, или оскорблением своих чувств вы пусты и жалки. когда человек находит себя и становиться целым в душе. он сжимает кулаки и разгребает день ото дня своё дерьмо. принимает всю жесткость и несправедливость мира. это больно, это тяжело, порой кажется не выносимо. но что есть то есть этим устоям тысячи лет.

меня давно это не трогает. я обрёл себя. нашёл. мне плевать кто, что скажет обо мне, моей жизни, мыслях или вере. у меня внутри есть, сука, стержень. у меня есть истории в жизни, от которых любое "меньшенство" тоже может пустить слезу. но я не тыкаю в мир своим говном. я его разгребаю. и ищу что то ценное в нём.

будьте не поколибимы, попытки исправить общество для будущих поколений всегда розят лживым эгоизмом, попыткой придать значимости жизни, которой мы за миллионы лет так и не познали....

когда жизнь белого мужчины натурала катиться впизду. все говорят "ну что такого, обычное дело". но если этот мужчина спит с другим мужчиной то "о боги, ублюдошное общество как ты смеешь??? надо помочь ему!!!" я не жалуюсь. люди прикрывающиеся толерантностью, или оскорблением своих чувств вы пусты и жалки. когда человек находит себя и становиться целым в душе. он сжимает кулаки и разгребает день ото дня своё дерьмо. принимает всю жесткость и несправедливость мира. это больно, это тяжело, порой кажется не выносимо. но что есть то есть этим устоям тысячи лет.

меня давно это не трогает. я обрёл себя. нашёл. мне плевать кто, что скажет обо мне, моей жизни, мыслях или вере. у меня внутри есть, сука, стержень. у меня есть истории в жизни, от которых любое "меньшенство" тоже может пустить слезу. но я не тыкаю в мир своим говном. я его разгребаю. и ищу что то ценное в нём.

будьте не поколибимы, попытки исправить общество для будущих поколений всегда розят лживым эгоизмом, попыткой придать значимости жизни, которой мы за миллионы лет так и не познали....

text:
just sitting there, with my body, on my gorgeous couch. 
the last few days i’ve seen news about activists photos being stolen and posted on a pornsite, police are involved, but we all know that it’s difficult. many (both men and women) blame the activists, the women who posted the photos. saying that it’s their own fault for posting photos online to begin with. we need to stop victimblaming! just stop! it is never the victims fault, never! i hate, hate, hate this patriarchy, i really do!
a few years ago, me and a friend did a free the nipple photoshoot, in public. we spoke on the radio and talked about why this is important, different kinds of activism to fight these power structures that objectifys and hurt women, for us to be seen as humans. 
because after this some of us (me included), were also posted on pornsites. men calling us feminist-cunts, sharing information about us, objectifying us. 
when these things happen, it speaks loud and clear about how far away from equality we are. 
but we will not be silenced, these are our bodies, our voices, our minds and our lives. men do not own us, we are human beings, our bodies belong to us and we deicide what we want to do with them. we are not here for you to deem us as fuckable or not, we don’t exist for you. and i’ll keep repeating this: men, we ain’t buyin your crap, no more!

tweet_full:
just sitting there, with my body, on my gorgeous couch. 
the last few days i’ve seen news about activists photos being stolen and posted on a pornsite, police are involved, but we all know that it’s difficult. many (both men and women) blame the activists, the women who posted the photos. saying that it’s their own fault for posting photos online to begin with. we need to stop victimblaming! just stop! it is never the victims fault, never! i hate, hate, hate this patriarchy, i really do!
a few years ago, me and a friend did a free the nipple photoshoot, in public. we spoke on the radio and talked about why this is important, different kinds of activism to fight these power structures that objectifys and hurt women, for us to be seen as humans. 
because after this some of us (me included), were also posted on pornsites. men calling us feminist-cunts, sharing information about us, objectifying us. 
when these things happen, it speaks loud and clear about how far away from equality we are. 
but we will not be silenced, these are our bodies, our voices, our minds and our lives. men do not own us, we are human beings, our bodies belong to us and we deicide what we want to do with them. we are not here for you to deem us as fuckable or not, we don’t exist for you. and i’ll keep repeating this: men, we ain’t buyin your crap, no more! 
#feminism #thisiswhyweneedfeminism #activist #bodylove #stopvictimblaming #womenarehumans #mentakeresponsibility #hairyfeminist #purplehair #vintagefashion #70sstyle #kroppsaktivism #metoo #fuckthepatriarchy #fightsexism #sisterhood #systerskap

text:
“since trump took office, the women of congress have become use to making public messages. they wore white to his inauguration and wore black to the #sotu in 2018 to show support for the #timesup and #metoo movements. this year, they all wore suffragette white yet again in solidarity with women all over. this coupled with their collective clapping and cheering when the accomplishments of women were mentioned, garnered quick criticism.
⚢🔥
a meme began surfacing claiming that these women were told what to wear and when to clap. it paid no regard to the meaning behind their fashion nor what they were all clapping for. it condemned them for making their own choices and celebrating their accomplishments as women. ⚢🔥
society would much rather tell a woman how to act and condemn her when she falls astray than let her make her own choices. this double standard has to stop. i can guarantee you that if it were then men in congress all coordinating some sort of message they would be praised for it. for their heroism and speaking out. but a woman? no way.
⚢🔥
the message the women of congress shared should be celebrated. this action showed the intersectionality of our fight as feminists. the camaraderie and sisterhood displayed at this year’s #sotu is inspiring. we have more strong women in congress that represent diversity and that is something that should be talked about. ⚢🔥
it’s 2019 and women aren’t here for your petty double standards” #linkinbio
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
sabrina by nick drnaso
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
what do you do when a loved one goes missing? sabrina leaves her home one day in chicago and that is the last time anyone (nice) sees her. soon after, a video surfaces on the internet that clarifies her whereabouts and leaves her family and boyfriend grappling with the ultimate grief.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
with quiet, subtle precision, drnaso sheds a light on the obsessive conspiracy theory culture that makes up some of the dark corners of the internet (coincidentally, also the same space where alt-right whack jobs that host radio shows can be found). he correctly points to the sad reality of our times where motivation to churn out, and profit from, negative content seems to be at an all-time high.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the only graphic novel to have been considered by the man booker prize (longlisted in 2018), sabrina is an important, albeit heartbreaking, read especially in the era of online trolling, “alternative facts” and maga hats. rating: 5/5.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#mjdoeslife #mdl #sabrina #nickdrnaso #manbooker #metoo #graphicnovel #art #feminist #feminism #bookstagram #booktube #goodreads #vsco #vscocam

text: i was late opening bibi moon @bibimoonboutique yesterday because i was having a ridiculously fun, absolutely silly, and completely thought provoking conversation with a room filled with 6 amazing women, and 2 brave sweet boys... @jimjefferies @theovon ✨the common denominator was my incredibly amazing customer and friend lauren @lro_senberg 👑she asked me to come to this meeting to discuss feminist issues with a couple of men who were friends of a comedienne whitney @whitneycummings and wanted feedback from strong opinionated women about their upcoming acts in the age of #metoo etc...as part of the pilot for her show man up on @comedycentral . while i am actually uncomfortable with being called a feminist because that word is so heavily charged with connotations & associations that i don't feel further the empowerment and equanimity of women, but in fact can alienate both sexes and ultimately end conversations and block dialogues that seek to illuminate and unite-i am a lifelong female who bears scars from decades on the battlefield of fighting to live my life in an way that has been criticized, negated, berated, belittled because i have followed paths, that if i had been a man would have been called adventurous and brave, but instead were deemed irresponsible, selfish, and just plain crazy. ✨✨ln the end, i didn't contribute much to the conversation, i was happy just to be a fly on the wall basically listening and laughing non stop to the group. ✨yet, i walked away with this tremendous sense of compassion for these two men (who revealed themselves to be incredible sensitive, vulnerable and confused in this world of women and surprisingly shared very personal details of their lives + upbringing) as well as a renewed understanding that men are all little boys (lots of potty & penis talk...)who are perhaps desperately seeking sex, but ultimately approval, attention, affirmation, adoration, and above all, love....which as women,gives us enormous power-and the more we acknowledge and own our feminine power, if we play our "cards" right, we will find greater and more equal footing in this world, and harmony. ✨after all, love is the highest common denominator of us all.

text:
something i'm working on..hard to get past the first few lines it taken a while for me to write what i have so far( literally just the first couple sentences)the rest is all freestyle because it's still something painful to write about sometimes just speaking what s on my mind and reflecting back to my mind at that young age helps me manage my emotions before i really put down the hard work into my finished song. i'm not rushing this one to finish, it's my process to cope with unsettled memories and reflect on ways i can improve my mind and heart. so i just thought i'd share the idea of what i'm trying to do with this beat and hopefully help someone else know there not the only ones and it's okay to still feel your pain after all these years don't stop living!and start loving❤ 💭🎶 .
.
.

text:
🖤why men’s mental health?🖤 i’m not going to lie to you guys. the past couple of months has sucked research wise. i was relying on a couple of universities for support and funding. i bent over backwards. i jumped through hoops. i compromised. i nearly downright buckled under their demands, but in the end, it never materialised. “there isn’t enough funding...current uncertain economic climate...brexit...” it was a gut punch.

now that i’m a few weeks down the line  i’m bloody glad it all fell through. this research isn’t going to waste away in some library. this research isn’t going to become confined to just statistics that ignore real life. this research is going to be about real men with real stories in the real world.

this research is going to be user-led. how many other research projects are like that? none. that my friends, is really fucking exciting.

i thought about giving up though, i really did. then @grifton_and_me got in touch and asked why i chose to focus on men’s mental health;

1. i have 4 brothers. but with their friends around our house all the time i really have 10 brothers. i like men. 😍

2. my brother has depression, anxiety and when younger, social phobia. this experience really shaped who i am today.

3. when working with schools i connected with the lost, forgotten boys. i was their champion then. i want to be their champion now.

4. #metoo

why do you support men’s mental health?

text:
how hard is it to change the world? ✨
it has been proven that children do not lie about being sexually abused. at the same time, statistics show that only about a quarter of those accused of abusing a child get arrested - let alone prosecuted or convicted.
✨
our county had almost a thousand children with reports of abuse last year. according to this statistic, 750 of those children would not have had their abuser arrested.
✨
most children never tell they are being abused. can you imagine what happens to a child that does tell and then their abuser is believed instead of them?
✨
what happens to the abuser? well it is also proven that most abusers will continue to abuse until they are stopped.
✨

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the cou documents.

michelle nichols

text:
tw/cw: #sexualassault #rapeculture #metoo #stockholmsyndrome .
.
.
i don't know how many of you are truly prepared to know the amount of people that you know that have been sexually assaulted. the #metoomovement put it into perspective for a lot of people, but do you really know how common place sexual assault is?

here's my experience:
a month before my sixteenth birthday, i was sexually assaulted to a very extreme extent, by someone i had known my entire life. my abuser has since passed away. i was vocal about it, until my entire family called me a liar. then, i shut up; i didn't like rocking the boat as a kid, and as a teenager, the rebellion streak hit me very, very late. i kept quiet again until i met my ex-fiancé, whom i confided everything in. instead of truly believing me, he set about psychologically conditioning me instead. he had become close with my abuser, and after asking him about my allegations, he learned things, never sharing them, instead using them to abuse me himself. i became his subservient, not through my own will, but through the manipulation of my dependency issues, my fragile and decaying mental health, and past traumas. i would do whatever he asked if me, as he was all i had, and if you asked me in 2009, all i needed. he eventually left me in 2012, when his brainwashing started to wane; i matured very quickly while with him, and he pushed me enough to break free of the limits he had imposed on me. whether this was his intention remains a mystery i don't care to solve. i'm a different person now in every sense of the word, though, because of what happened on 2/13/06. i am not broken or weaker because of the things i've been through, i'm stronger, and smarter. i have been irreparably damaged by the things i was subjected to by these two men in particular, but i have had a bakers dozen of encounters of men groping, harassing, stalking, and assaulting me since then.
the last guy got socked.
im making progress with every guy i check.

it's been 13 years. and this is the first full public statement. but not the last.

thank you, @courtwithconfidence
for giving me the confidence to share my story!

#dontstayquiet #endrapeculture

i do not know how many of you are truly prepared to know the amount of people that you know that have been sexually assaulted. the  put it into perspective for a lot of people, but do you really know how common place sexual assault is?

here's my experience:
a month before my sixteenth bihday, i was sexually assaulted to a very extreme extent, by someone i had known my entire life. my abuser has since passed away. i was vocal about it, until my entire family called me a liar. then, i shut up; i didn't like rocking the boat as a kid, and as a teenager, the rebellion streak hit me very, very late. i kept quiet again until i met my ex-fiancé, whom i confided everything in. instead of truly believing me, he set about psychologically conditioning me instead. he had become close with my abuser, and after asking him about my allegations, he learned things, never sharing them, instead using them to abuse me himself. i became his subservient, not through my own will, but through the manipulation of my dependency issues, my fragile and decaying mental health, and past traumas. i would do whatever he asked if me, as he was all i had, and if you asked me in 2009, all i needed. he eventually left me in 2012, when his brainwashing staed to wane; i matured very quickly while with him, and he pushed me enough to break free of the limits he had imposed on me. whether this was his intention remains a mystery i do not care to solve. i am a different person now in every sense of the word, though, because of what happened on 2/13/06. i am not broken or weaker because of the things i have been through, i am stronger, and smaer. i have been irreparably damaged by the things i was subjected to by these two men in paicular, but i have had a bakers dozen of encounters of men groping, harassing, stalking, and assaulting me since then.
the last guy got socked.
im making progress with every guy i check.

it is been 13 years. and this is the first full public statement. but not the last.

thank you, ouwithconfidence
for giving me the confidence to share my story!

 notstayquiet

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text: this is the first time in 30 years that the state legislature is holding a hearing on sexual harassment. the #metoo moment has revealed what many of us have known for far too long - that sexual harassment is pervasive across all sectors of the economy and that we as a society and as a legislative body have a tremendous amount of work to do to make all workplaces safe for all workers. today's hearing is long overdue, and should signal the beginning but not the end of an ongoing conversation about the steps that we must take today and every day to ensure that women in the workforce can reach and exceed their full potential.

text:
a safety plan is a living document that outlines how your family plans to keep your children safe from sexual abuse. it is not merely a list of "rules", but it is a lifestyle that incorporates behaviors that family members and non-family are required to adhere to if they are going to continue to have access to your child. your safety plan will change as your child grows and matures to incorporate safety behaviors that align with their activities outside of the home as well as social responsibilities regarding the opposite sex. an example of a few of these behaviors might include....
1) children are not forced to show affection to anyone.
2) children don't sit in the laps of family or friends.
3) children are always clothed during playtime with adults or other children.
4) if a child asks you not to touch them, their request is respected. 
5) children are taught that they should not be asked to keep secrets by any adult. explain the difference between secrets and surprises.
6) children should not be behind closed doors with teachers, coaches, or church leaders.
7) consent is required before touching another child. this includes kissing and hugging.

if you appropriate vernacular, culture, style of hair/dress, dance (or try to) but do nothing in the face of atrocities committed against black women (see #sandrabland and countless otbers), you are part of the problem!! but, if you want to disrupt the status quo and be a change agent, then be vocal, stand up. especially, you, black man. if you're white, then use your privilege, because yes, you have it, and yes, it's important to be an ally.

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
#wien - morgen ist #wiederdonnerstag ✊🏼💞🔥
.
bei unserem 17. do-date treffen wir uns um 18 uhr am platz der menschenrechte. .
hier bei der auftaktkundgebung sprechen @aikokazukokurosaki über die arbeit von @obra_onebillionrisingaustria - nima obaro und lisa dallinger vom verein peregrina über migrantisch-feministische selbstorganisierung und die rassistische vereinnahmung von gewalt gegen frauen sowie die journalistin sarah nadj über die bedeutung von #metoo für sie und was davon geblieben ist.
.
anschließend gehen wir in einer demonstration über den getreidemarkt, den karlsplatz, die operngasse und die margaretenstraße zur schlusskungebung am margaretenplatz. 
für die musik während der demonstration sorgen alecid und bydl - @hausgemachtinwien und @dj_countessa (brunnhilde)
.
auf der schlusskundgebung am margaretenplatz sprechen beate neunteufel-zechner von der initiative ehe ohne grenzen über transnationale beziehungen und die schwierigkeiten, mit denen binationale paare konfrontiert sind sowie marissa lobo und elijah* über liebesbeziehungen, die über heteronormativität hinausgehen.
.
die redebeiträge werden wieder simultan in die österreichische gebärdensprache (ögs) gedolmetscht.
.
den regierenden, nutznießer*innen und mitläufer*innen werden wir ausrichten: "ihr werdet euch noch wundern, wer da aller für liebevolle, vielfältige beziehungsweisen kämpft.”
🔥💞✊🏼💖💯
.
musik: lassie singers
.
#fixzam #resist #donnerstagsdemo #smashpatriarchy #liebe

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
i made a post that asked the question, “how do you navigate flirtation in the #metoo era?” and this question was directed to men. the reason i posted this is to open the conversation to see how men might be learning or struggling with this topic. and it’s true, some men are scared of flirting because they don’t want to be accused, and it needs to be talked about amongst men. i realize that i also have women who are part of my audience and that asking this kind of question has impact, and on a social media platform like facebook/instagram, it makes it an open forum. i welcome the opinions and i’m grateful for the voices. .
.
.
this blog is a response, calling on men to be responsible for developing their emotional intelligence as a response to the #metoo movement, to doing the work of calling each other in, and supporting each other to heal toxic masculinity. it is uncomfortable work, but it must be done.
.
.
.
click on the link on my profile to read the blog. 
#rafaelmartinezcoaching #lifecoach #menswork #masculinity #relationships #relationshipgoals #toxicmasculinity #femininerising #realtalk #metoo #shadowwork

text:
i set off on a mission to not only see parts of the world that i wanted to see but to also write a book detailing my life story.  i believe that i had done the impossible and that is not hubris. i believe that i have been able to tap into a place of human potential that most cannot and the reason that i decided to write a book laying out my past and how i got to be the person i am today is because i know that if i can do it then anyone can.

now to the point. my blog will no longer be a “digital nomad” blog because honestly, i don’t give a shit about being a digital nomad. i wanted to share my experiences in the world and i feel like i did that to the best of my ability. i am going to let this blog simply be what it is and that is whatever i feel like writing or sharing.  maybe writing a book and traveling the world qualifies as being a nomad but honestly, i’m more interested in sharing my truth in a different way. i subtitled this blog traveling through trauma because i anticipated coming out the other side a different person. i’m only getting started and nothing is the same.

that’s it. that’s all i got right now. it’s midnight in vietnam and i’m going to eat peanut butter and listen to tool because that shit makes me happy. -m

if you want to read the rest the link is in my bio.
