text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text: crying out loud is the new short film from director tatia pilieva which captures a fresh perspective on male vulnerability through honest conversations. like her groundbreaking films first kiss and undress me, crying out loud explores the human condition: "i was interested in shedding light on changing landscape of masculinity in the #metoo & #timesup era while creating a compassionate portrait of an emotional man. i was particularly curious about capturing men crying - both vulnerability and sincerity behind the tears and also crying as a metaphor for putting traditional masculinity to rest.” hit the link in our bio to watch the film in full and to read tatia's accompanying essay via little black book. #pulsefilms #tatiapilieva #cryingoutloud #masculinity #film @lbbonlinepix

text:
📸📸📸
from ➡️ @thetipsymuse 
super super late to this #ginsourchallenge and i was nominated by brenton @cheerstohappyhour.  but hey i am doing it.  here is a gin sour named "changing tides" that i made at home based on the recipe from @elixirsf.  i had it at elixir a few weeks ago and fell in love with it immediately.  the gin used in this drink is a sea gin right from here in oakland california, automatic sea gin @oaklandspirits, briny with foraged nori, sage and lemongrass.  so many possibilities with this one!
.
.
.
changing tides by the talented natalie lichtman @nataliethecatalie via @elixirsf
.
2 oz oakland sea gin @oaklandspirits
. 
0.75 oz fennel syrup
.
0.75 oz egg white
. 
0.25 oz pineapple juice
. 
0.5 oz lime juice
.
garnish: candied fennel seeds from @shakerandspoon .
.
.
method: fizz tall, with soda, expel lemon oils and discard
.
final tip: i like to add one ice cube to the final drink to keep it chill. a little trick i learned from @pch580.
.
.
.
thanks for thinking of me, brenton.  this drink is still available at @elixirsf til end of this month.  i am looking forward to seeing the new menu starting in october. .
.
.

text:
i just came across this beautiful comment left by @sarahjaynepie on the post i wrote for @spoonie_village 😭🥰✨ ⠀
⠀
•⠀
⠀
"really enjoyed reading sarah’s piece on art and healing. strangely it was a read i felt drawn to - see what i did there? 🤦🏼‍♀️ been exploring photography recently and discovering mindful moments in capturing images of the clouds through my bedroom window. i’ve always wanted to learn how to take a wonderful picture, something my dad was very skilled at before lewy bodies dementia took hold recently...⠀
the need to capture the peace i feel in those sky-gazing beautiful minutes and have that moment at hand as a sort of mini mindful practice has been helping me hugely in the last few weeks. i’m trapped in some sort of cfs/me/fibro mania and just can’t rest my mind. lots of looping and rumination going on to add to the bloody back pain and random stabby bits with physical and mental exhaustion to blame, but i really do feel that through photography i’m calming my body- even if just for a sunset moment. it’s funny how we seem to find our creativity when we need it the most. a most welcome beautiful distraction 📷🌄 "
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀

text: tried to catch a rainbow today 😂. didn’t work but i still love trying. maybe that’s a metaphor for love somehow lol. to all my sisters and brothers who’ve gone through caca and survived, rock on loves. i wish you the best as you move forward in this crazy thing called life. i met a woman this weekend who’s having a really hard time getting past her trauma. i sincerely empathized with her state of mind and being. being caught up in it is so hard... and at first glance you wouldn’t know she was so traumatized. she looked like a typical oc housewife type. but within minutes of meeting her she admitted her truth and i’m just a caring stranger... it was sign of how much the pain of it all is on her mind. it’s right there for her with every breath, poor lady. so let’s try this. let’s challenge each other to a no judgment week! let’s be open minded to people we come across daily and try to swipe the judgement to the side. don’t judge the clothes or makeup or lack of either. just chat. see if you can see where someone else is coming from. i challenge you!!!!! let me know if anything exciting happens 😂. ❌⭕️❌⭕️vu❤️💜 #vaginasunitedvu #ourdaughtersarewatching #yourvoicematters #metootimesup #metoo #metooisvu #timesup #believesurvivors #metoomovement #endrape #rapeculture #rapecultureiswhen #rapecultureisreal #womensmarch #believewomen #keepfighting #truth #metoostories #abuseawareness #endrapeoncampus #enoughisenough #whyididntreport #yourvoicematters #familyviolence #itsnothyourfault #womenunited #womenpower #womenempowerment #nomeansno #survivor

text:
dios es mujer... you go girl!
.
algo está cambiando en el mundo... los movimientos feministas emergen con fuerza en este 2019, y sí, sé que existen desde el siglo xviii, con muchas vertientes y puntos de vista diferentes, unos más radicales que otros. pero esta vez, han tomado el mundo digital como principal impulsor. como muestra, en el 2018 vimos importantes movimientos como #metoo y el #timesup que sin duda hicieron temblar a los poderosos que parecían intocables.
.

estamos mucho más concientes sobre el concepto y lo que representa. las marcas, como agentes sociales, se han sumado a la oleada de feminismo que recorre el mundo, y han lanzando campañas convirtiéndo esto en un fenómeno ya conocido como femvertising, es decir, campañas publicitarias relacionadas directa o indirectamente con el feminismo y sus causas.
.

el feminismo está de moda, pero aquí el problema surge cuando esta tendencia puede ser vista por las consumidoras como oportunismo desde una perspectiva del marketing, y no como un apoyo a una causa. porque aunque muchos lo duden, hablarle a un mercado femenino no es tan fácil como parece. aquí, la importancia radica en la coherencia... y las mujeres somos extremadamente intuitivas para detectar el engaño.
.
. ¿qué opinas?  te leo
.
.
.
#estrategia #maryfrancia #marcapersonal #marketing  #carteldelmarketing #ohhcontenido #feminismo

text:
often when i do an intake and ask why someone has chosen to seek treatment now, i hear: i want to be a better parent/significant other. those are great reasons, but wanting to just feel better for yourself is a great reason too! sometimes therapy is solution focused to fix a specific problem. sometimes therapy is to increase happiness even when you can’t find a specific problem. whatever your reason for coming, you will be accepted, you will be heard, and you will be helped! 
www.thrivewcma.com
contact@thrivewcma.com
978-291-8243
#mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealth #breakthestigma #timesup #metoo #depression #anxiety #ptsd

text:
*
- say your sorry*
- correct yourself in front of those who follow you.*
- humble yourself*
- let someone else shine, you don’t always have to be the center of attention.*
- be a life-long learner*
- read books, listen to podcasts, and watch shows  about cultures and people who don’t look or act like you*
- get to know people who don’t look or act like you.
- be more concerned with how you make people feel rather than how you appear! *
- be quiet and listen!*
- say hello*
- have integrity. stop faking it. let what you do behind the scenes be a reflection of what you do in front of other people! *
- take responsibility*
- follow-up. return a phone call or an email in a reasonable time! *
- practice self control!*
- be open and share your struggles and weaknesses*
- ask for help when you need it! get counseling. step down if you need to, until you get better.*
- practice self-care and self-compassion*
- pray*
- be kind*
- surround yourself with people who will tell you the truth.*
- connect others to opportunities*
*
*
*
my heart goes out to ann marie miller who was sexually abused when she was 16 from a southern baptist youth minister. i heard her story on @npr. *
*
we need leaders who truly follow the ways of christ. not those who chase after their sick and twisted desires! *
*
i am praying for leaders to rise up and do the right thing!
name: Diana Patton

text:
assalamualaikum semua..
untuk tournament pes19 maaf yea korang.. dah full slot.. untuk mobile legend korang boleh baca di bawah tuu..
welcome to mobile legends

terima kasih kerana berminat menyertai pertandingan kami yang bertempat di kluang mall rooftop, kluang mall, kluang johor . pada 16 feb 2019. dari 10am hingga tamat. 
diingatkan kepada yang ingin turut serta , sila baca dan patuh syarat serta arahan terlebih dahulu sebelum anda mendaftar dan melakukan penbayaran bagi mengelakkan salah faham di hari kelak .

jika anda mempunyai squad yang bagus , ingin menjadi seperti air asia saiyan , icon , evos , saiyan reborn dan sebagainya . ayuh !!! serlahkan kehebatan , skills dan strategi pasukan anda . disinilah bermulanya pemain professional . ayuh ! tunggu apa lagi . *ikuti cara² utk mendaftar*

1.sila bank in yuran penyertaan terlebih dahulu di akaun : *upper class men resources no.akaun: 551137526613 (maybank)*. sila rujuk pada penganjur terlebih dahulu untuk membuat bayaran .

2.kemudian maklumkan kepada penganjur bahawa pembayaran telah dibuat , *ambil gambar & simpan resit original anda* .

3.sila *double confirm* betul² maklumat pasukan dan ahli anda sebelum mengisi borang tersebut . kesalahan dan kecuaian anda sendiri boleh mengakibat pasukan anda maklumat tidak diterima & tidak dibenarkan bertanding sama sekali .

4.sila submit borang & bayaran anda *serentak pada waktu yang sama* . slot adalah terhad , sebarang rayuan dan bantahan tidak akan dilayam sama sekali .

5.sila berikan butiran seperti berikut
1- nama pasukan
2- nama pemain (no ic) (no id ml)
3- pasukan mestilah memberikan 6 nama pemain (1 simpanan)
4- setiap pasukan dikenakan yuran pendaftaran sebanyak rm60 shj.

jom daftar sekarang
slot adalah terhad

untuk mendaftar pasukan anda sila hantar maklumat pasukan ke no whatapp 0177878388
segala masalah sila pm en rossi utk keterangan lanjut.
name: KETEGAQQ STUDIO

text:
i don’t know where to begin, other than to begin slightly overwhelmed and say i am 1000% honored to have sat nude for the highly talented painter @danielmaidman as he painted my portrait.  a few years back, in 2013, when i was living in chicago, i painted a piece titled “power pussy” that generated quite a bit of controversy.  daniel has known me since then and we’ve maintained a great friendship. i believe i may have been joking with daniel at one point about him creating a second version of "power pussy," loosely based on the original powerful statement pose, and it quickly (in painting time anyway, over the course of a year and a half), became a reality.  thank you daniel, for giving me my head in this portrait, since in the original i left it off as a commentary about the hyper sexualization of women in our culture. this portrait feels powerful, yet soft. it feels bold, yet romantic.  it feels contemporary, yet timeless.  daniel captured my soul in this piece and it’s at once frightening, and not, as it feels as if i’m just staring into a mirror.  during the process of him painting i decided it’d be a great idea to dig in with an interview, and ask questions about his process, life and how he feels being a painter in the modern era.  you don’t want to miss his perfectly stated answers (he is after all a highly skilled writer as well), so please click the link in my bio and give the full video a watch. the finished painting can be seen right at the end.  thanks as always for watching. .
.
.
.
.
.

what books are you looking forward to reading in 2019? 📚
stay up with hugo best by erin somers is an incredibly timely, terrifically witty and moving debut about a young writers’ assistant on a late night comedy show and what transpires when she accepts an invitation from its enigmatic host to spend a long weekend at his mansion in connecticut.
at once hilarious and poignant, brilliantly incisive and terrifically propulsive, stay up with hugo best is an incredibly timely exploration of sexual politics in the #metoo age, and the unforgettable story of one young woman’s poignant stumbling into adulthood.

text:
tomorrow! join us for a valentine’s day seminar hosted by @pncacriticalstudies 
jasmine johnson
thursday feb 14 from 11:00-12:30, hammer conference room

me too; now what? 
we've heard their stories, we've told our own but when and how does the healing begin?  jasmine, licensed clinical therapist,  provides an introduction to the journey to addressing and healing from all forms of sexual violence and violations.  this will jumpstart participants understanding and motivation to begin to work through the traumas associated with sexual harassment, rape, molestation, violence, and sexually inappropriate behaviors.  while the movement against those that violate has been a huge collective step, many are left with an open wound that affects them daily.  this seminar is designed to address and validate triggers, and offering coping mechanisms for sexual trauma; as well as for family, friends, and community allies wanting to provide support. 
jasmine johnson-decosta, the owner of blue pearl therapy llc, has been providing therapeutic services in a variety of settings for over 15 years. she has been fulfilled at helping clients work through challenging times and reach their goals. jasmine is a solution-focused therapist with an emphasis on a strength-based approach. her clients are able to identify their own strengths, resiliency, and resources to improve any situation causing distress. jasmine has extensive work with clients living with post traumatic stress disorder (ptsd), medical illness and injury counseling, military/civilian sexual trauma, veteran and caregiver related stressors. #metoo #jasminejohnson  @bluepearltherapyllc

text:
what does politics have to do with psychology? 
things that were once kept as private confusion have now risen to the surface through issues that are personal and impact us deeply. both at home in the workplace, these choices impact our families and their security. healthcare, non disclosure agreements, forced arbitration are all now common issues. 
changes on a macro level are hard to come by when repeated issues cannot be made public, “will never be seen by a jury” means that there is little incentive for change (just google google). it also adds to emotional labor on a daily basis.

text:
today, i’m feeling grateful that at a young age—i was introduced to legally documenting every interaction that i had with my abuser. 
_____________________________________
i’m grateful that at the age of 12—i would lock myself in a closet and pour through depositions and evidence exhibits that i stole in order to keep one step ahead of my abuser trying to steal me out of the country. he already told me that a judge would never believe me—that i was crazy—that i didn’t have the “right perception of reality” as i locked and barricaded my bedroom door one last time with him screaming. 
________________________________________________________
i’m grateful that at the age of 13—i was forced to go to counseling with my abuser. it taught me that people would rather believe a respected male figure—than believe the girl with fire in her eyes. ________________________________________________________
i’m grateful to all the men who have beaten, grabbed, strangled, drugged, raped, or catcalled—and then joked and called me a cunt for using my words to silence their abuse. it taught me that a good punch to the throat was always a solid move if you didn’t want to hear their raw sewage of words pour out. 
_________________________________________________________
and i could keep going. we only really got up to the teen years.
___________________________________________________________
but what this really all means—is that in 3 days—i’ll have a total of 24 years of experience in fucking shit up and taking names. 
___________________________________
and that feels really, damn good. 
here’s to the best birthday ever 💛

text:
india is full rapist, indian villages do what ever they want, and india does nothing, couples are paraded naked, raped, and murdered, every day, like aarav and sophia, rip.
-
-
on january 16, 2019, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, aarav, 19, and sophia, 18, got married and were cousins but there family, did not like it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, raped, and killed by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, raped and murder. rajasthan kept the names of the attack hidden. the attackers are only in jail for 3 years. shame on india, rip aarav and sophia.

text:
via @wtopnews: there were 46 deaths from domestic violence in maryland between july 2017 and june 2018. the victims were remembered in a ceremony monday night, presided by maryland first lady yumi hogan. “as a mother and a grandmother, my heart breaks for the victims of these senseless tragedies,” hogan said.

the maryland network against domestic violence says 26 intimate partners were killed, including wives, girlfriends, husbands and boyfriends.

among the dead were five bystanders, including off-duty prince george’s county police officer mujahid ramzziddin who was killed when he rushed to the aid of his brandywine, maryland neighbor.

fifteen abusive partners died, 10 of them were men in murder-suicides. “what we know is that it can and does happen in communities all across maryland regardless of socio-economic status, racial makeup and all other kinds of demographics,” said inga james, president of the maryland network against domestic violence.

the names of domestic violence victims were called and participants at the ceremony displayed each name on red heart-shaped signs, which also indicated the victim’s cause of death. guns were used in 67 percent of the killings. “this can happen anywhere. it can happen everywhere. it happened here,” said senator chris van hollen, d-md.

van hollen said it’s important to remember the victims of domestic violence and support survivors and the loved ones of the victims.

the maryland network said the victims who lost their lives in the 12-month period left behind 35 children.

do you stand with me?

text: hey, idk how to start this but i’m posting this because i want people to get aware of happening, not because i want attention and not because i want people to feel sorry for me. i was raped. like soooo many other girls. i already posted this on my private account but it feels good tbh to tell people and not to stay quite. i felt like it was my fault for such a long time because a lot of people made me feel like it’s my fault with them saying things like “why didn’t you just say no?” or “it can’t be that bad when you waited so long to tell everyone” things like that make you feel so bad and that’s probably the reason so many girls stay quite about it. rape is never someone’s own fault and there are no excuses for it. if you experienced sexual violence or anything like that i’m here if you want to talk. i’m still learning how to handle everything and i’ll never forget what happened but i’m going to learn how to live with it. also a huge thank you to the people who supported me still support und help me. #stopthesilence #metoo

text:
“be mine” 💔
for my last valentine’s day look i wanted to do something a little different. while this is a touchy subject it’s something people go through everyday. abusive relationships, sexual assault, harassment are things that will mostly happen to everyone in their life. even though it’s hard and you might even love someone. if you’re in an abusive relationship you need to get out of it because you might think it won’t happen again or i can fix this.. the likely hood of it stopping is very unlikely.. step back and put yourself in your mom or dads shoes and if they knew everything would you want to stay with this person? just know youre are amazing and brave and you’re not alone and that you don’t deserve this, abuse is never your fault and everyone gets mad sometimes but talking about it is the way to sort it out❤️❤️ i hope everyone’s safe on valentine’s day and of something wrong speak up❤️ #metoo

text:
sometimes after a sexual assault or sexual abuse- your best option is to sue the perpetrator or the institution involved in the abuse for money to pay for your therapy or for money to show that they harmed you- to right a wrong. 
learn more about this process in the latest episode of slut or nut: the podcast, with personal injury and sexual assault/abuse lawyer simona jellinek.

most of these civil lawsuits result in a settlement for the survivor- which with the conviction rate in criminal trials being so low- sometimes a cash settlement can be more beneficial to the survivor than a two year jail sentence for the perpetrator or worse- no conviction at all. 
episode available on
 #soundcloud #itunes #youtube and #stitcher.

tweet_full:
sometimes after a sexual assault or sexual abuse- your best option is to sue the perpetrator or the institution involved in the abuse for money to pay for your therapy or for money to show that they harmed you- to right a wrong. 
learn more about this process in the latest episode of slut or nut: the podcast, with personal injury and sexual assault/abuse lawyer simona jellinek.

most of these civil lawsuits result in a settlement for the survivor- which with the conviction rate in criminal trials being so low- sometimes a cash settlement can be more beneficial to the survivor than a two year jail sentence for the perpetrator or worse- no conviction at all.

text:
so much and yet not enough of our focus is on self: self care, selfishness, self doubt, etc. what shouldn’t get lost through it all, trend or not, is the fact that true change does originate within ourselves. for example, people cannot quit smoking “for” another person but must want it themselves. similarly, changing negative thought patterns requires a deep and honest dialogue with yourself. if you can’t admit what you may or may not be doing to impede changes, you can’t truly say you’ve tried everything you can to make improvements.
.
this has been a hard concept for me, not because i can’t be honest with myself but because i realize i didn’t ever dig deeply enough to challenge why or how i react a certain way.
.
as i learn more about the various emotions that feed into our actions, i see a bit more clearly that part of being honest with myself is acknowledging the feelings, however selfish or unreasonable they might seem to me, that may have driven me to react in a particular way.
.
i have always prided myself on my logical nature and it is an important portion of my ability to be honest and practical about my goals. however, emotions are not usually very logical. they’re the adjectives and filler that complete the story and fill in the blanks for our brains to make sense of the world around us.
.
reality and our perception of reality can easily get blended together into a confusing knot. being more in tune with myself is not intuitive for me and is going to continue to be something i have to integrate more completely into my life.
.
but the first step starts with me.
.
.
.
.
.
#intjfemale #mentalhealthawareness #onedayatatime #change #depression #anxiety #metoo #ibelievesurvivors #metoomovement  #timesup #nyc #balance #self #selfcare #wellness #endthestigma #twft52

text_retweet:
#repost @valenciagunder
・・・
"florida legislators, no matter their party — and no matter their gender — have shown a heartening amount of empathy for incarcerated women on an issue that affects them, uniquely. 
on monday, the state senate criminal justice committee unanimously approve the dignity for incarcerated women act. the legislation would guarantee that women behind bars have free and unlimited access to hygiene products.
it’s not an issue that makes the front pages. however, prison beatings — and murders — sexual assaults and bribery are not the only indignities to which prisoners are subjected. finding their voices in the era of #metoo, advocates say that women in jail, prison, holding facilities and even juvenile detention, depend on the whims of prison guards who might withhold sanitary items, giving them a few tissues instead — or nothing at all. often, the women are forced to buy such basic necessities in the prison store."
#dignityflorida #reform #newfm #mwc #nlirj #cut50 #womensmarchfl #plannedparenthood #ff4l
#increase #moderndayfannielou

text: the unconscious survival mechanism of doubt. chapter 19 "we all know these people, and maybe we can recognize some of these traits in ourselves. the naysayers, the killjoys, the skeptics. the blamers, and complainers, the procrastinators and those who always have big plans that never come to fruition. because to have a negative view on life means that you’ll never be unexpectedly disappointed. to expect failure means that you’ll never feel broadsided, and to never finish anything means that you can’t be criticized—because no one can criticize something that you didn’t put out there for others to see. if we respond to any of life’s uncertainties with doubt, we have the illusion of safety and control, even if it isn’t conscious. the trap is that we end up criticizing ourselves, which fuels the doubt and fear we bring to life’s uncertainties even more—and we get stuck in a trap that is damaging one person and one person only. ourselves." #healing #badass #trauma #community #yoga #meditation #women #metoo #mindfulness #men

#cyberharassmentawareness:

spreading false information about an individual: up to 3 years in prison or up to rs. 1 million in fine or both.

whoever intentionally and publicly displays any information through an information system, which he knows to be false and intimidates or harms the reputation or privacy of an individual, shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or with fine which may extend to one million rupees or with both:

for example:

you know that a piece of information is wrong and you still post or share it on facebook about a person that damages his/her reputation

text:
the first time i heard the words “forgive” and “abuser” used in the same sentence in a directive manner to me by my coach, i thought “no fucking way! no fucking way am i going to forgive the person who abused me. what he did was wrong. .
how could i forgive him for what he did?! i don’t want to forgive him!”
.
she interrupted the rant in my head suggesting that i not only forgive him but i also find the gift in the abuse. i broke my silence, “gift? what the hell kind of gift will i ever find in the abuse? there isn’t a gift in that.”
.
“julie, hurt people hurt people. when people are hurt, they lash out and hurt other people – sometimes consciously and other times they have no idea they are even doing it. since he was hurting you it’s likely someone was hurting him, because what he did to you is not normal behavior. what he did to you comes from a hurt person.”
.
up until that moment i never had the thought he had been abused or hurt by someone and therefore abused me. i finally understood the phrase hurt people, hurt people. however my new understanding didn’t ease any of my pain or make me want to forgive him.
.
then she put a cherry on top sharing the quote: “holding onto anger is like drinking poison and expecting the other person to die.” (unknown)
.
what i learned after that is forgiveness is a process, and it was a process for me, not him. although it wasn’t easy to forgive, over time i forgave him.
.
.
.
.
.
#forgiveness #forgivnessforall#timetoforgive #letgoofanger #releaseanger#hurtpeoplehurtpeople #metoo#metoomovement #forgivenessisaprocess#othersideofmetoo #sundayslowdown

.
up until that moment i never had the thought he had been abused or hurt by someone and therefore abused me. i finally understood the phrase hurt people, hurt people. however my new understanding didn’t ease any of my pain or make me want to forgive him.
.
then she put a cherry on top sharing the quote: “holding onto anger is like drinking poison and expecting the other person to die.” (unknown)
.
what i learned after that is forgiveness is a process, and it was a process for me, not him. although it wasn’t easy to forgive, over time i forgave him.
.

text:
$140 investment. 
made over $500 my first month $27,000 my first full year.

over the past 5 years this opportunity has become something i never imagined possible for me- but i built belief in myself because i watched my mentors before me do it, so i knew what was possible… i shifted my mindset to -“ if she can do it, so can i!” ask you this friends, what would adding in an additional income to help with bills, family fun, or spoiling yourself every now and then do for you?

i totally get it, how challenging it may seem to add something else into your life when you’re probably already working a full-time job, and have tons of obligations and responsibilities- #metoo when i signed up february 2014- i was already working a full time, with a commute- i had two small children and three manson, found out we were expecting our third- i knew it was going to take sacrifices to build this- and that i was going to have to develop myself in ways i never had to make this work- i had concerns, like what if it didn’t pan out? but i’ll be honest… i couldn’t afford not to do this! i was short on tile and money- i was anxious, depressed and craving more out of life!

so when someone says they can’t afford theinvestment (that literally pays for your own workouts and product to make you healthier) ... i have to ask... how can you afford not to?? over the past five years, our lives have changed drastically… we’ve seen success, and been able to do things we never believed would be possible… i’m on a mission to pay that forward… our team is continuing to grow, and i’m expanding my mentor ship to nine more women this month, who are ready to transform their lives, and get healthy from the inside out, while building a business that can take them to a completely different level and add so much value to their lives for their family! if you are ready, to go all lynn, get uncomfortable, and build something meaningful… drop your name below or shoot me a message and i’ll get you all the details- make 2019, the year that you stop wishing, wanting and wondering… and just freaking go for it!

text:
standard valentinstag war gestern – 2019 machen wir aus einem tag der paare und des konsums einen abend für feminist*innen und ihre freundi*nnen. 💕👭 wir laden euch ein, den blick auf die frauen* im theater zu richten und inspiration aus der freien szene zu ziehen. 👀

wir werden über geschlechtergerechtigkeit im theaterbetrieb reden und uns fragen: entstehen hier strukturen und ästhetiken, die den männlichen blick und die patriarchalen hierarchien ablegen? oder zahlen die macher*innen für ihre selbstbestimmtheit mit prekären arbeitsbedingungen und die katze beißt sich in den schwanz? 🎭🤔 anschließend schauen wir uns gemeinsam das stück „phobos“ der choreografin maura morales an. danach gibt es ein publikumsgespräch mit ihr, der dramaturgin katja grawinkel-claassen und den künstlerinnen. 🙌 
meldet euch jetzt an unter clara.marx@fft-duesseldorf.de! 💕 der eintritt für den stammtisch ist frei. bitte bei der anmeldung angeben, ob ihr auch ein ticket für das stück „phobos“ (für teilnehmer*innen kosten dieses 9€) wollt. .

#fftduesseldorf #freiestheater #theaterfrauen #metoo #andshewaslikebäm #feminism

good morning all! 🇺🇸 we are happy to announce that the drug lord joaquín “el chapó” guzmán has been found guilty of all counts that he was charged with in his involvement in the mexican cartel. el chapó shipped billions and billions of dollars worth of drugs into the united states as a leader in the mexican cartel for over 25 years, killing many of our citizens, and he is expected to be held at supermax prison in florence, colorado- dubbed by many as the most secure prison in the entire united states. 
_____________________________________________________
you may be asking yourself “why is ted cruz in this image as well?” well, ted cruz has an interesting proposal for what the us government should use el chapo’s money for: the “el chapó bill” seeks to use all of the drug lords 14 billion dollars that has been confiscated to pay for the wall. we will have to see how this bill holds up when it enters congress...

text:
// what a perfect day (see my previous post) to introduce you, dear readers, to the world of tudor women. historical fiction books and biographies have proved to be a great platform to to pen down women’s voices, who for centuries, have been suppressed. after all, history is written by the victors and those who had most power. through novels about women like us, who lived in highly patrarchal times, we not only hear his-story, but her-story. it is so appropriate to read women’s side of history, not to mention in current times influenced by feminism and the #metoo movement. let us read and listen to some remarkable women so that past mistakes don’t repeat themselves in the future. •••

text:
when i was a little younger, like in middle school, i had this notebook which said “she needed a hero, so that’s what she became” on the front. i always really resonated with that, and it was sorta my mantra for quite some time. while “hero” is far more than a stretch, it’s that energy that i’m trying to bring into the world. i believe everyone has a little bit of ‘save the world’ energy inside them, and i encourage y’all to tap into it. we are powerful, and it takes womxn like us to save the world. and if all you can save if yourself, that’s okay too. 
just some food for thought tonight. thank you for all the love.

text:
“leave safety behind. put your body on the line. stand before the people you fear and speak your mind--even if your voice shakes. when you least expect it, someone may actually listen to what you have to say. well-aimed slingshots can topple giants.” --maggie kuhn
…
from #metoo #timesup to #blacklivesmatter #nodapl #neveragain #heforshe #womensmarch #takeaknee #yeswecan and so many more relevant causes that pepper not only our social media feeds, but also our everyday conversations, we live in a time where your voice, your opinions, your beliefs can quickly be stated and shared.
…
whether you shared your personal story with #metoo, got a bucket of ice poured over your head from the #aslicebucketchallenge or you showed up and #womensmarch each of these were opportunities you chose to take a stand, to step-up for a cause you believed in. to let your voice be heard.
…
whether it’s on a grand stage or in the comfort of your own home, your voice always matters.
…
as humans, we are all different. we are raised in different times, in different households with different beliefs on religion, politics and just core values. these differences make the world go round. at the end of the day, you make your own truth and then live by it.
…
you don’t have to be perfect, brave or even speak loudly, what matters is that you open your mouth and say what you need to say when it needs to be said. you don’t have to agree with everyone all the time, you can agree to disagree. what you do have to remember is that the power of your voice has meaning and holds truth.
…
is there something you’ve been holding inside, biting your tongue because you’re not sure if you’ll be understood or received well if you do open your mouth? maybe it’s time to take a breath, gather your thoughts and let your voice be heard.
…
love, light & laughter, suzy & shelley

// this really happened on february 13, 1542, in an age void of female rights and a #metoo revolution. this queen's story deserves to be heard... //
••• today marks 477 years since katherine howard, the fifth and youngest queen of king henry viii, was sent to the block, by said king, to face her death. it's been a long time since then, but her memory still lives on in our hearts. if there's one thing everyone should know, it is that affair or no affair, whether guilty or victim, she did not deserve to die; she was just human like me and you. none of us is without fault. and none of us deserves to be sent to death by our spouse, especially not without a court hearing. may katherine be remembered for all her good qualities. <3 •••

text: belen rodriguez, intervistata da la repubblica parla del perchè è partita per l'argentina, proprio ora che sembrava essersi riavvicinata all'ex marito, stefano de martino: "non sono venuta qui per la famiglia. sono in vacanza, avevo bisogno di un po' di tempo per me". e, a domanda diretta su se/come sta procedendo con de martino la showgirl pare non abbia voluto rispondere, anche se il "sono in un momento particolare della mia vita" ha, forse, parlato più di lei. e sarà ancora più eloquente il filmato integrale di belen e stefano, che verrà trasmesso questa sera a #cr4-la repubblica delle donne condotto da @pierochiambretti e @alfosignorini . belen ha parlato anche delle continue critiche cui è soggetta: "se sei bella sei anche cretina, non soffri, non provi dispiaceri come le altre donne. ma chi l'ha detto? mi sono stancata di agire con spontaneità e venire travisata". quanto, invece, alle recenti dichiarazioni di rocco papaleo (secondo cui belen durante il festival di sanremo condotto insieme rivolgeva parole solo sul palco, ndr): "non è assolutamente vero. chi mi conosce lo sa, io parlo con tutti". un palco, quello dell'ariston, che belen rivedrà a partire da venerdì, essendo nella giuria di sanremo young: "il festival è il programma a cui sono più affezionata (...), ma non giudicherò, darò la mia opinione ". anche se a livello professionale rimane maria de filippi il suo "mentore": "stare con lei è come fare una seduta di analisi, un'esperienza incredibile senza prezzo". sempre a livello professionale nell'era del #metoo vien da chiedersi e chiederle se sia mai trovata in situazioni di disagio: "mai in situazioni in cui devi scappare.. se un uomo ti apre in accapatoio risolvi non entrando nella stanza " ha risposto la showgirl e conduttrice che sul fututo ha detto "mi piacerebbe avere un altro figlio (dopo santiago che "viene prima di tutto", ndr.).non voglio che la mia vita sia particolare, voglio che sia normale". #spysee

text:
after last night's post everything is clicking. why did i start to run? why do i always focus on my legs? i feel like a missing piece has returned home. i feel like i can do anything right now. 
maybe telling these stories is super healing for me. all i did was act when i heard that little voice inside.

well there it is folks. maybe just telling your story will free parts of yourself you didn't even know were trapped 💛🦉🌹 thank you for reading & all the love + support 🌻

text:
good morning saints! “little children, let us not love in word or talk but in deed and in truth.” 1 john‬ ‭3:18‬ ‭esv‬‬. this passage starts out “little children,” with the understanding that the listeners have a lot to learn pertaining to this subject. we love to talk and be philosophical about scripture, but it also comes a time when you have to put what you learned into practice. the bible says: “but be doers of the word, and not hearers only, deceiving yourselves.” james‬ ‭1:22‬ ‭esv‬‬. you are only deceiving yourselves if you believe you are pleasing god without actually helping someone in some capacity. the scripture says let’s do everything in deed and in truth. and it also says we will worship in spirit and in truth. one is natural (deed), the other is spiritual (worship). they both have the same key element, truth, which is jesus christ. neither can be done and be pleasing to god without the son. so let’s not just talk about helping one another and actually do it, in jesus name, amen! stay blessed and faithful! 
pastor ken simmons

text: om prostitution behandlades som vilket yrke som helst, skulle en faktisk konsekvens bli att dom som står utan inkomst kan komma behöva söka jobb inom prostitution. prostitution som ”bransch” välkomnar alla och det finns inga kroppar som är för trasiga, för sjuka, för tjocka, för smala, för klena eller för ärriga för att handlas med för sexuella ändamål. för personer som inte är sk arbetsföra och som behöver ekonomiskt bistånd eller pengar från fk skulle alltså plötsligt prostitution kunna bli ett anvisat yrke. för som saknar utbildning eller meriter för att söka andra jobb skulle prostitution alltid vara ett tillgängligt alternativ, eftersom det inte finns några krav på den som säljer sex utöver ”ha en kropp” samt ”ta betalt för sexuella handlingar” och såklart även ”lydnad”. det finns argument som att personer ska ha rätt att göra vad dom vill med sina kroppar - alltså sälja dom om dom önskar - och man menar då att det är en rättighet och en frihet i det. men i ett samhälle där människor är skyldiga att försörja sig genom jobb om inte det finns särskilda skäl för varför inte blir jobb en skyldighet. rättigheten att sälja sin kropp kan existera utan att det måste vara ett yrke som alla andra. för om det vore ett yrke som alla andra skulle arbetssökande ha en skyldighet att söka även det yrket om alternativa inte finns. att sälja sex beror på yttre (ekonomiska, sociala) eller inre (psykiska) tvång  redan, för den absoluta majoriteten som säljer sig. men om att sälja sex var ett yrke skulle rätten att sälja sin kropp bli skyldigheten att göra det. och all form av hjälp att lämna prostitutionen för den majoritet som gör det som enda val skulle bortmonteras pga utsattheten ses som en rimlig försörjning. trots all forskning på dom psykologiska konsekvenser och på kroppsskador och våldsutsatthet personer i prostitution finns fortfarande argumentet att ”man ska få jobba med det om man vill”. men om man fattar politiska beslut efter en minoritet som vill att prostitution ska vara ett jobb av den orsaken missar man vad som är essensen i prostitution - mäns våld, mäns maktutövning och dominans samt (forts kommentarer) #prostitution #intedinhora #metoo

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer". in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field." despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
gloria allred ist frauenrechtlerin und führt eine anwaltskanzlei. ⚖ sie vertritt 33 frauen, die in einem prozess gegen entertainer #billcosby stehen. ihm wird sexuelle nötigung und versuchte vergewaltigung vorgeworfen. in einem ersten prozess wurde er verurteilt. 🚨 .

solche fälle sind für #allred nichts neues. denn seit 42 jahren vertritt sie frauen, die von reichen, mächtigen, berühmten männern schlecht behandelt wurden. lange bevor es den #metoo gab. 💪 .

in einem interview für die @zeit sagt sie: «bei frauenrechten war es immer so, dass man sich erst mal zwei schritte vorwärtsbewegt hat, dann aber wieder einen schritt zurück. die unterwerfung der frauen gehört nun mal zum status quo. wenn frauen, ermutigt durch die #metoo-bewegung, aufstehen und kundtun, dass es ihnen reicht, wird es leute geben, die den status quo bewahren wollen, weil ihre macht davon abhängt.» 🚺

#feminism #frauenpower #womenrights #timesup

text: the talisman................................................ the onus of healing is shoved upon victims, survival a daily "why" left dangling as though unharmed people think the same. they don't. those who walk without the pain and the clatter of scars are so free it friggin sings. the view from the out-side a technicolor movie i saw as a kid...the vibrant motion overwhelming and foreign. my eyeballs shrieked with both fear and joy, the surprising exuberance coming into the brain as the very first taste of ice cream while skating on a half-frozen lake. "surely, i would be lost if i fell in?" the colorful landscape so different than my real life i absorbed it only to the surface, an over-full sponge of someone else's barf having only so much room. the other way life is the talisman, a lushly vibrant, living, breathing, singing movie watched from the middle of a crowded theater.

#weightprivilege #weightidentity
"we never hear fat women's #metoo stories and it's not because they don't have them

it took me years to disclose my own experiences. because, like any woman, i knew that stepping forward would mean standard denials, scrutiny, dismissals. unlike other women, that resistance comes as a question: <<who would want to rape you?>> as a fat woman, my body was seen as inherently undesirable. any sexual attention fat women receive is treated as a windfall worthy of congratulations. fat women are expected to be grateful for any expressions that could be mistaken for want, including assault and harassment.”-lestat moore, orthodox calendar

text:
dagens #vågatasnacket går till powerkvinnorna bakom @raserietpodden som under manifestationen på sergels torg under #metoo (2017) framförde en kravlista till alla män. som i citatet kräver de att männen ska rannsaka de andra männen i sin omgivning, men även sig själva. 
de har dessutom dessa, helt självklara (men uppenbart måste det sägas) krav att ställa dem: * sluta ta på kvinnor du inte känner. * sluta tjata! sluta tjata till dig en dans, en kyss, ett telefonnummer, att ni ska gå hem tillsammans, att ni ska ha sex. * sluta ha sex med kvinnor som sover. * sluta ha sex med kvinnor som är för fulla. * sluta ha sex med kvinnor som inte visar på något sätt att de vill ha sex med dig. * sluta skratta med när dina vänner drar sexistiska skämt. * sluta förminska och ifrågasätta kvinnors vittnesmål om sexuella övergrepp. * sluta vara så rädd för att prata om dina känslor och tankar med andra män i din omgivning. * sluta säg ”inte alla män” när vi pratar om att nästan alla kvinnor har fallit offer för sexuella trakasserier och övergrepp. * sluta våldta oss för fan.

#vågatasnacket #raseriet #raserietpodden #metoo #metoosverige #våga

text:
medya özellikle kadın ölümlerine şüpheyle yaklaşmalıdır. çünkü bu ülkede kadın cinayetleri artarak devam etmekte ve cinayetlerin bir kısmı da "intihar etti" denilerek yok sayılmaktadır. medyada takip ettiğimiz üzere intihar ya da şüpheli ölüm olarak yaklaşılan birçok kadın ölümünün cinayet olduğu ortaya çıkmıştır. öldürülen, tecavüze maruz bırakılan kadınların, transların medya eliyle suçlanmaması, medyanın sansasyon yaratarak gereksiz röntgenci bir hazza hizmet edecek detaylarla rating elde etmesinden daha önemlidir. bu başlıklarla verilen mesajlar kadına yönelik ayrımcılığı derinleştirir ve kadınların bir yerlere giderek öldürülmeyi "hak ettikleri" mesajını topluma iletir. bir kadının şüpheli ölümüyle ilgili verilecek bir haberde vurgulanması gereken noktalar, “plaza, doğum günü, günlük kiralık daire, lüks otel balkonu, lüks villa” vb. değil, o kadının orada nasıl ve kim tarafından öldürüldüğüdür. haberlerinizde cinayetleri meşrulaştırma çabası yerine gerçekleri araştırın!

text:
"emma ist hübsch und beliebt, die jungs reißen sich um sie. und sie genießt es, versucht, immer im mittelpunkt zu stehen: das mädchen, das jeden herumkriegt. bis sie nach einer party zerschlagen und mit zerrissenem kleid vor ihrem haus aufwacht. klar, sie ist mit paul ins schlafzimmer gegangen. hat pillen eingeworfen. die anderen jungs kamen hinterher. aber dann? sie erinnert sich nicht, aber die gesamte schule weiß es. sie haben die fotos gesehen. ist emma wirklich selber schuld? was hat sie erwartet – emma, die schlampe in dem ultrakurzen kleid?"
.
das ist die inhaltsangabe zu 'du wolltest es doch' von louise o'neill.
das buch war für mich echt krass, aber auch so gut, dass ich mich in emma hineinversetzten konnte. es geht um victim blaming, also opfer-beschuldigung, und um slut-shaming, also um das schämen des opfers, der sch*****.
es ist ein buch zur #metoo debatte, das wichtig ist und das wirklich gut umgesetzt wurde.
➡️ habt ihr es gelesen? und wenn ja, wie fandet ihr das buch? zu krass? oder fandet ihr es authentisch, oder gar zu authentisch?
ich würde gerne eure meinung dazu lesen!
.
.
#bookish #bookstagram #instabooks #instabook #books #askingforit #duwolltestesdoch #carlsenverlag @carlsenverlag #louiseoneill #buch #book #rosen #bookandflowers #roses

text: ett inlägg med både hopp och inspiration! sen januari 2016, när mitt yrkesfokus gick från preventionsarbete kring srhr- och sexualitetsfrågor till maskuliniteter har det hänt saker. lite väl långsamt för min smak, särkilt om vi jämför med hur det satsas tid, engagemang och kapital på teknologi- och miljöfrågor. ett bra exempel på vad som händer är om vi tittar mot våra grannar i finland. @ekvalita har ett skolprojekt om hur vi gör efter #metoo med utgångspunkt att förändra destruktiva maskulinitetsideal. den bygger på fyra insatser. 1. skolbesök i klasserna, 2. samarbete med engagerade pedagoger, 3. samarbete med pedagogiska fakulteten, 4. manliga nätverk. utöver det projektet händer det en hel del bland frivilligorganisationer som @manforjamstalldhet och @rfsu . keep the hope om en värld där #metoo blir en #neveragain #maskulinitetsnormer #allamän #jagtrorpåmän
name: Marco Vega • Sexualupplysare

text:
❣️i’m off to train our wales team on the importance of personal lived experience stories for charities. .
.
🕊why it needs to be meaningful and not tokenistic, and how it can be an incredibly empowering experience for everyone involved.
.
.
🗯sharing the impact that sexual and domestic violence has had on my mental health via a blog on @mentalhealthfoundation website a year ago was really scary. 🖕🏻i knew i wanted to do it to show i wasn’t silenced - and because the more of us that speak without shame, the more of us will realise we are not alone in our feelings. .
. 
this is why i’m modelling our gorgeous green ribbon - the international symbol of mental health awareness. so that any one who passes me knows that it’s okay to talk about mental health, and that however they feel today i accept them 💚
.
.
#pinitformentalhealth #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #sexualviolence #domesticviolence #metoo #posttraumaticgrowth

text:
making healthcare prices transparent and affordable: president trump wants to work with congress to increase price transparency, end surprise billing, offer more options, and lower costs.

tonight, president trump announced his commitment to take action to increase price transparency so as to prevent surprise billing and empower consumers.
hospitals, insurance companies, and drug companies should be required to disclose real prices to patients in order to drive costs down.
the president has taken action to curtail the cost of healthcare by empowering patients, expanding options, and increasing competition.
the administration’s expansion of health insurance options are already reducing premium costs for many americans after the ballooning increases caused by obamacare. #itsastart 
#fixit  what a/b those who’ve had their  #healthcare taken — no fault of their own— , then priced out  of the market and seniors on fixed incomes?
#20% of #americans with existing conditions still  don’t have  #affordable #options #available to them. #metoo

text: 5am thoughts....filling myself with hate was never an option. but holding onto the pain, on the other hand, was my weakness. internalizing what happened and feeling like i had to go through it alone turned into depression and thoughts of suicide that i have battled all of my life. in my later years, i am able to see things from a more mature perspective. i know that i can’t hold onto things and that i need to just forgive, but when i say this, i do not mean forget. use the pain for inspiration, for art, for exercise, writing, for a template on how not to treat people. we learn from other people’s mistakes just as often as we learn from our own. #selflove #abuseawareness #speakout #childabuseawareness #pray #metoo #overcome #strength #forgivenessisfreedom #soulsearching

a little magic happened last night....scrolling through fb and this image caught my eye. 
double take..... ‘is that my book there?’ yep definitely ‘let’s go home’ sitting there in the front row of @theellenshow ellen degeneres birthday basket! ‘oh the places she’ll go!’ @natashagilmoureditorial and i so often laughed about the power of halia, we knew she would land in exactly the right place at exactly the right time. 
and this one had nothing to do with me - it was a complete shock! i knew nothing about it and i wasn’t even tagged in the photo so it was pure chance that i found out. 
like i said, definitely some magic happening here, which was always going to happen when your books are published by @karenmcdermottpublisher @makingmagichappenpress ✨✨✨ i’m still pinching myself! thank you @hollywoodswagbag @celebrityhollywoodgifting for this awesome surprise 🙏

text:
de liefde en ik
.
ik weet niet beter als dat ik mijn hele leven al aan het zoeken ben naar liefde, “de liefde”. ik heb, opgroeiend in ons gezin, deze liefde gemist.
thuis had ik geen goed voorbeeld omdat mijn ouders vanaf dat ik geboren ben altijd ruzie maakten. zij hadden een haat/liefdes verhouding waardoor er weinig liefde aanwezig was. mijn moeder sprak vaak slecht over mijn vader, wat hij allemaal fout deed, wat ze niet van hem kreeg, bij hem miste en dat ze eigenlijk weg wilde bij hem.
.
mijn vader heb ik, daardoor een lange periode op afstand gehouden. ik gaf hem de schuld dat alles in ons gezin niet lekker liep. dat er zoveel ruzie was en wij ons ongelukkig voelden enz
tegen mijn moeder zei ik, na elke ruzie met mijn vader, wat zowat elke dag was, dat zij weg moest gaan bij hem. dan zei ze weer: ik wil niet dat mijn kinderen zonder vader opgroeien.
dat begreep ik dan niet, want nu hadden wij ook geen liefdevolle vader, geen liefdevol thuis. er was elke dag ruzie, strijd en ongemak.
.
mijn moeder had zichzelf al lang geleden verloren. bleef hangen in het patroon van ruzie maken zonder hierin verandering te brengen. om het heft in eigen handen te nemen en te kiezen voor geluk, haar geluk. in plaats daarvan schuilde ze achter haar “negatieve” overtuigingen, dat haar kinderen een vader moesten hebben in hun leven. nu begrijp ik dat mijn vader geen echte vader kon zijn door het toedoen van mijn moeder. dat heb ik heel lang niet kunnen zien.
.
wanneer je de les van de liefde nog niet geleerd hebt, kopieer je als het ware wat je hebt meegemaakt in jou huidige (liefdes)leven. je trekt een soortgelijke vrouw/man aan die dan een spiegelbeeld is van je vader/moeder.
je creëert een gezinssituatie / liefdesrelatie die in principe hetzelfde is als hoe het was in je opgroeiende jaren. je hebt het zo als voorbeeld gekregen van je ouders en dat is 'normaal ' voor jou, je weet (onbewust) niet beter.
.
.

text:
festa della donna
.
mercoledì 6 marzo 2019 dalle ore 20:00 alle 23:00
c/o associazione 585, via crea 25, spinea (ve)
.
conferenza e cerchio di condivisione sulla violenza psicologica
.
in occasione della festa della donna, in un periodo in cui l'attenzione dei media spesso è rivolta ai femminicidi e alla violenza fisica sulle donne, sentiamo l'esigenza di approfondire anche un altro tipo di violenza, più subdola e quasi sempre invisibile: stiamo parlando della violenza psicologica, che colpisce moltissime donne e che spesso viene sottovalutata, pur avendo conseguenze devastanti.
molto spesso, la vittima non si rende nemmeno conto di essere tale finché non si rivolge a un medico e/o a uno psicoterapeuta per curare un insieme di malesseri dei quali ignora la causa (ad esempio insonnia, disturbi alimentari, depressione).
.
anche allora, il percorso per uscire da una situazione di violenza psicologica è lungo e richiede l'intervento dei centri antiviolenza e, molto spesso, il sostegno di una terapia psicologica.
.
crediamo sia importante diffondere il concetto di abuso psicologico, non solo per capire in cosa consista e quali conseguenze possa avere, ma anche quali siano i rimedi legali e il supporto che le autorità possono fornire per uscire da una relazione tossica in sicurezza, senza cadere vittime del senso di colpa.
.
dopo la conferenza, tenuta dall'avvocatessa anna bellon, si terrà un cerchio di condivisione e, come di consueto, una cena a cui ognuno contribuirà con una pietanza dolce o salata.
.
contributo per la serata: offerta libera e consapevole.
.
nell'occasione sarà possibile iscriversi all'associazione "casa della dea" per poter partecipare a tutti i nostri eventi.
.
per altre info contattate anna al 348-8188734.
è gradita conferma! .
link all'evento in bio
.
.
.

text:
been watching @nbcsvu with @therealmariskahargitay , @kelligiddish , @icet , @peterscanavino etc. from the very first ep and was always a fan. 
but this last season got me thinking; in fact, i got thinking ever since the 2nd trans avery got murdered. and in season 20, #oliviabenson keeps sabotaging vics, even getting them murdered. good going, benson! but this is known, so i'm not getting into how problematic benson is.

my main beef is that svu would not protect me. because i am fat. what? look at the vics! by far most are white, 99% are slim, and, other than the old ladies in the nursing home episode, pretty much 100% are what society considers attractive. fat, "ugly", old, or non-white vics clearly don't feel encouraged to report their rape in the svu universe - or they're just not worth raping to begin with? because clearly, hardly any people fitting that description are vics on that show. or is it that shit american tv does - insist that everyone be pretty?

either way, it makes not-so-pretty survivors like me feel abandoned by the ever so vocal message of the show. i imagine that vics of colour can relate. or vics with visible disabilities (who aren't redeemed by a pretty face), deformities, the elderly... i mean, even child vics are picked from pretty aisle, because even victims of child abuse gotta have an appearance that explains why the perp picked them, huh? pimple-covered, fat, four-eyed (native american/black/asian) kids don't get groomed oh wait they do, but not on svu. i remember that being fat with shitty skin didn't save me, not at 7 and not at 27.

the fact that this show only depicts pretty and predominantly white and able-bodied, young-ish vics, and as such, only depicts pretty folks as worth protecting/as vulnerable, is utterly offensive and discouraging given #metoo & general gender- and sex-based violence & discrimination, because this show sure as hell discriminates – hey, viewer's wouldn't want images of a screaming, naked fatty.

#lawandorder #lawandordersvu #nbcsvu #specialvictimsunit #mariskahargitay #kelligiddish #icet #sexualassault #waronwomen #rapeculture #survivors #fatphobia #womenofcolor #feminism #ineedfeminismbecause

text:
natürlich kenne ich alice schwarzer, habe simone de beauvoir gelesen und #metoo verfolgt. aber ich habe tatsächlich auch zu den frauen gehört, die der meinung waren,  wir sind frei und gleichberechtigt. dass der weg aber noch nicht zu ende und feminismus nicht old-school ist, sondern notwendig und aktueller denn je - das habe ich leider erst nach dieser augenöffnenden lektüre erkannt.
.
ich habe mich in den einzelnen abschnitten immer wieder gefunden - als hesse-lesenden teenie, der sich damals so frei gefühlt hat, ohne zu wissen, wer diesen weg geebnet hat. und ohne zu ahnen, dass gerade mal 1977 der mann seiner frau noch verbieten konnte, arbeiten zu gehen, "falls dies mit ihren pflichten in ehe und familie nicht zu  vereinbaren sei". wtf? erkannt habe ich mich auch im kindergarten, als die erzieherin mich gegen meinen willen aus der matchboxecke gezogen und in die puppenstube bugsiert hat. in aussagen von mitmenschen, die mir jetzt erst als unglaublich abwertend erscheinen. und wieso gibt es das wort "karrierefrau", aber nicht "karrieremann"?
.
ich hätte dieses buch gerne meinem 20jährigen ich überreicht. um weniger wegzulächeln und stärker haltung zu beziehen. mehr fragen zu stellen und zu diskutieren. nicht so oft "eigentlich" zu verwenden und vor allem früher zu erkennen, dass meine eigenen fähigkeiten gut und genug sind.
.
ich nehme aus diesem buch alle sätze mit. viele impulse. und das intetesse, mich mehr mit feminismus zu beschäftigen. lest es. unbedingt.
.
.
.
.
#margaretestokowski #rowohlt #rowohltverlag #untenrumfrei #literaturliebe #literatur #feminism #feminismus #bookstagramdeutschland #bookstagram #leseliebe #buchliebe #buchliebhaberin #booklover #buchliebe #buchnerd

text:
si vous avez suivi les derniers événements sur les réseaux sociaux, vous avez probablement entendu parler de la “ligue du lol”... un petit groupe de journalistes et communicants - essentiellement des hommes - ayant moqué, humilié et harcelé des consoeurs par le biais des médias sociaux plusieurs années durant et ce en toute impunité. ces trolls en costume m’ont inspirés une petite publication. 
vous savez, dans mon entourage, il y a de nombreuses personnes assez sceptiques sur l’intérêt des réseaux sociaux pour usage personnel et c’est ce genre de scandal qui enlève du poids à mes arguments. pourtant, je suis convaincue qu’ils sont réellement utiles. .
qu’est-ce qu’on aurait manqué sans les réseaux sociaux ? .
> les milliards de soutiens pour des pétitions et manifestations indispensables 🌍♻️
> les fantastiques projets et crowdfundings entièrement financés 🌈
> les élans de solidarité lors des terribles événements terroristes à travers le monde (ex : à paris #porteouverte) 👋🏼
> les milliers de groupes d’entraide sur facebook (ex : wanted community) 🧠
> les personnes, animaux et même doudous, ayant été retrouvés 👶🏼🐶
> les gens ayant décroché un emploi (dont certains en situation de précarité extrême) 💼
> les marques green ou éthiques nées sur instagram grâce au développement et l’encouragement de leur communauté 🌿
> les mouvements #metoo #bodypositivity #selfcare #objectifbikinifermetagueule #zérodéchet & co qui transforment positivement notre société 🌞
> parfois, une rencontre déterminante, professionnelle ou personnelle 💫
> je vous laisse compléter... 😃
.
ceci n’est bien sûr qu’un maigre échantillon non représentatif ! 
des success stories sur les médias sociaux, il y en a assez pour qu’on ait envie d’y rester. les réseaux sociaux sont fantastiques, c’est l’usage qu’en font certains qui peut-être écoeurant... puisqu'il s'agit d'un amplificateur. d’ailleurs cela concerne tout l’internet. nous devons noyer des types comme ceux de la #liguedulol au milieu d’un océan de belles histoires 😉 le digital est un incroyable accélérateur de solidarité et de créativité, à nous de faire en sorte que nos usages soient le reflet de la meilleure part de notre humanité !

text:
ça se passe au bureau, au parking, dans l'ascenseur, dans le secret d'un cabinet médical ou une salle de classe, lors d'un entretien d'embauche ou d'un déplacement (ah ! les séminaires...), après un déjeuner ou un dîner qui ont créé les conditions du passage à l'acte, brusqué, consenti. ou pas...
à l'opposé d'un énième essai sociologique sur le monde de l'entreprise ou d'une vision d'expert des rapports humains, "l'amour au bureau" donne la parole à de "vraies" gens qui témoignent sans tabou de leur expérience, encouragés par la méthode de l'auteur : un entretien en toute liberté et sans fausse pudeur, une relation de confiance entre enquêteur et interviewé(e), de l'humour, de l'émotion, aucun jugement.

sortie  en librairie le 14 février ! disponible en précommande.

https://laboiteapandore.fr/2019/02/08/lamour-au-bureau/
